{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860779186,"sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","part":{"id":"prt_d798d05de001G8gq15zTBadh7I","messageID":"msg_d798cf694001lEh3lhRVWJr4gs","sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a00d4cacbfa5462eb1acd83b46ac0df1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Purpose**: Extend PicoD file management capabilities with Kubernetes client-go integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through custom Kubernetes resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: PicoD file management API provides secure file operations within isolated workspace jails. AR-016 enhances this by integrating with Kubernetes through the generated client-go library, allowing PicoD instances to be managed as Kubernetes resources while maintaining existing HTTP-based file management APIs. This integration enables lifecycle management, health monitoring, and workspace orchestration at the Kubernetes level.\n12: \n13: ### Key Requirements\n14: \n15: - Maintain existing HTTP-based file management APIs (upload, list, download)\n16: - Integrate with Kubernetes client-go for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n17: - Support workspace provisioning and management through Kubernetes custom resources\n18: - Enable health status reporting to Kubernetes via status subresource\n19: - Provide watch/informer capabilities for real-time resource updates\n20: - Maintain workspace jail security and path sanitization\n21: - Support graceful shutdown and cleanup of workspaces\n22: - Enable multi-tenant isolation through namespace separation\n23: \n24: ## Architecture\n25: \n26: ### Package Structure\n27: \n28: ```\n29: pkg/picod/\n30: ├── auth.go                    # JWT authentication (existing)\n31: ├── execute.go                 # Command execution (existing)\n32: ├── files.go                   # File management handlers (existing)\n33: ├── server.go                  # HTTP server (existing)\n34: ├── handlers.go                # HTTP handlers (existing)\n35: ├── middleware.go              # Middleware (existing)\n36: ├── errors.go                  # Error handling (existing)\n37: ├── config.go                  # Configuration (existing)\n38: ├── constants.go               # Constants (existing)\n39: ├── k8s_integration.go         # NEW: Kubernetes client integration\n40: ├── workspace_manager.go       # NEW: Workspace lifecycle management\n41: ├── status_reporter.go         # NEW: Status reporting to Kubernetes\n42: └── informer.go                # NEW: Resource informers and event handlers\n43: \n44: changes/AR-016/\n45: ├── design.md                  # This document\n46: ├── spec.md                    # API specification\n47: ├── CHANGE.md                  # Change log\n48: └── IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md  # Implementation summary\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Component Interactions\n52: \n53: ```\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                        Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n56: │                                                                          │\n57: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n58: │  │                   API Server                                     │   │\n59: │  │  - AgentRuntime CRD                                              │   │\n60: │  │  - CodeInterpreter CRD                                           │   │\n61: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n62: │                                │                                        │\n63: │                                │ REST API                               │\n64: │                                │                                        │\n65: │  ┌─────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n66: │  │                 PicoD Controller (Optional)                       │  │\n67: │  │  - Creates/updates AgentRuntime resources                         │  │\n68: │  │  - Manages PicoD instance lifecycle                               │  │\n69: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n70: │                                                                          │\n71: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n72:                                   │\n73:                                   │ HTTP API (JWT Auth)\n74:                                   │\n75: ┌─────────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n76: │                          PicoD Instance                                  │\n77: │                                                                           │\n78: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n79: │  │              HTTP Server (Gin)                                  │     │\n80: │  │  - /api/execute                                                │     │\n81: │  │  - /api/files (upload, list, download)                          │     │\n82: │  │  - /health                                                      │     │\n83: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n84: │                                  │                                        │\n85: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n86: │  │         Kubernetes Client Integration                           │     │\n87: │  │  - Clientset for Runtime API                                    │     │\n88: │  │  - Informers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter                   │     │\n89: │  │  - Status reporting (UpdateStatus)                              │     │\n90: │  │  - Watch events (Add, Update, Delete)                           │     │\n91: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n92: │                                  │                                        │\n93: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n94: │  │         Workspace Manager                                       │     │\n95: │  │  - Workspace provisioning                                       │     │\n96: │  │  - Path sanitization and jail enforcement                       │     │\n97: │  │  - File operations (upload, list, download)                     │     │\n98: │  │  - Cleanup and garbage collection                               │     │\n99: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n100: │                                  │                                        │\n101: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n102: │  │         Status Reporter                                         │     │\n103: │  │  - Health status aggregation                                     │     │\n104: │  │  - File system statistics                                       │     │\n105: │  │  - Resource usage metrics                                       │     │\n106: │  │  - Error conditions and events                                  │     │\n107: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n108: │                                                                           │\n109: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n110:                                   │\n111:                                   │\n112: ┌─────────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n113: │                    Shared Workspace Volume                                │\n114: │                                                                           │\n115: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n116: │  │         Workspace Directory                                     │     │\n117: │  │  - User files                                                   │     │\n118: │  │  - Code artifacts                                               │     │\n119: │  │  - Execution outputs                                            │     │\n120: │  │  - Temporary files                                              │     │\n121: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n122: │                                                                           │\n123: └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n124: ```\n125: \n126: ### Request Flow with Kubernetes Integration\n127: \n128: ```\n129: 1. Kubernetes Resource Creation\n130:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n131:    │ User/Controller creates AgentRuntime CRD instance           │\n132:    │                                                              │\n133:    │ apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1           │\n134:    │ kind: AgentRuntime                                           │\n135:    │ metadata:                                                    │\n136:    │   name: my-agent                                             │\n137:    │   namespace: default                                         │\n138:    │ spec:                                                        │\n139:    │   image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agent:latest                   │\n140:    │   workspaceSize: \"1Gi\"                                       │\n141:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n142:                            │\n143:                            ▼\n144:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n145:    │ Kubernetes API Server validates and stores the resource     │\n146:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n147:                            │\n148:                            ▼\n149:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n150:    │ PicoD Pod scheduled with AgentRuntime reference             │\n151:    │ Environment variables injected:                             │\n152:    │ - AGENTRUNTIME_NAME, AGENTRUNTIME_NAMESPACE                 │\n153:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n154: \n155: 2. PicoD Initialization\n156:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n157:    │ PicoD starts and initializes Kubernetes client              │\n158:    │                                                              │\n159:    │ - Loads in-cluster configuration                            │\n160:    │ - Creates clientset for Runtime API                         │\n161:    │ - Starts informers for AgentRuntime resources               │\n162:    │ - Retrieves corresponding AgentRuntime resource            │\n163:    │ - Provisions workspace directory                            │\n164:    │ - Starts status reporter goroutine                          │\n165:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n166: \n167: 3. File Management Operations (HTTP API)\n168:    POST /api/files\n169:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n170:    │ HTTP Request (JWT authenticated)                             │\n171:    │ - Upload file to workspace                                   │\n172:    │                                                              │\n173:    │ PicoD processes:                                             │\n174:    │ - Validates JWT token                                        │\n175:    │ - Sanitizes file path                                        │\n176:    │ - Writes file to workspace                                   │\n177:    │ - Updates workspace statistics                              │\n178:    │ - Triggers status update (async)                             │\n179:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n180: \n181: 4. Status Reporting (Async)\n182:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n183:    │ Status Reporter periodically updates Kubernetes             │\n184:    │                                                              │\n185:    │ - Collects file system stats                                 │\n186:    │ - Aggregates health status                                   │\n187:    │ - Calls client.UpdateStatus()                                │\n188:    │                                                              │\n189:    │ Status subresource updated:                                  │\n190:    │ status:                                                      │\n191:    │   phase: \"Running\"                                           │\n192:    │   workspace:                                                 │\n193:    │     fileCount: 42                                            │\n194:    │     totalSize: \"1024MiB\"                                     │\n195:    │     lastModified: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"                     │\n196:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n197: \n198: 5. Watch Events (Informers)\n199:    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n200:    │ Informer receives events from Kubernetes                    │\n201:    │                                                              │\n202:    │ - AgentRuntime deleted → Cleanup workspace, shutdown        │\n203:    │ - AgentRuntime updated → Apply configuration changes        │\n204:    │ - ConfigMap changed → Reload configuration                  │\n205:    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ## Data Structures\n209: \n210: ### Kubernetes Client Integration\n211: \n212: **File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration.go`\n213: \n214: ```go\n215: // K8sClient manages Kubernetes client operations\n216: type K8sClient struct {\n217: \tclientset       *agentcubeclientset.Clientset\n218: \tagentRuntimeClient runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInterface\n219: \tcodeInterpreterClient runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInterface\n220: \tnamespace       string\n221: \tagentRuntimeName string\n222: \tinformerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n223: \tstopCh          chan struct{}\n224: }\n225: \n226: // K8sConfig holds Kubernetes client configuration\n227: type K8sConfig struct {\n228: \tInCluster      bool\n229: \tKubeconfigPath string\n230: \tNamespace      string\n231: \tAgentRuntimeName string\n232: \tAgentRuntimeNamespace string\n233: }\n234: \n235: // NewK8sClient creates a new Kubernetes client\n236: func NewK8sClient(config K8sConfig) (*K8sClient, error) {\n237: \tvar kubeConfig *rest.Config\n238: \tvar err error\n239: \n240: \tif config.InCluster {\n241: \t\tkubeConfig, err = rest.InClusterConfig()\n242: \t} else if config.KubeconfigPath != \"\" {\n243: \t\tkubeConfig, err = clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", config.KubeconfigPath)\n244: \t} else {\n245: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"either in-cluster or kubeconfig path must be specified\")\n246: \t}\n247: \n248: \tif err != nil {\n249: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n250: \t}\n251: \n252: \tclientset, err := agentcubeclientset.NewForConfig(kubeConfig)\n253: \tif err != nil {\n254: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n255: \t}\n256: \n257: \tnamespace := config.Namespace\n258: \tif namespace == \"\" {\n259: \t\tif config.InCluster {\n260: \t\t\tnamespaceBytes, err := os.ReadFile(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/namespace\")\n261: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n262: \t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to read namespace from service account: %w\", err)\n263: \t\t\t}\n264: \t\t\tnamespace = string(namespaceBytes)\n265: \t\t} else {\n266: \t\t\tnamespace = \"default\"\n267: \t\t}\n268: \t}\n269: \n270: \tinformerFactory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, time.Minute*10)\n271: \n272: \treturn &K8sClient{\n273: \t\tclientset:            clientset,\n274: \t\tagentRuntimeClient:   clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace),\n275: \t\tcodeInterpreterClient: clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace),\n276: \t\tnamespace:            namespace,\n277: \t\tagentRuntimeName:     config.AgentRuntimeName,\n278: \t\tstopCh:               make(chan struct{}),\n279: \t\tinformerFactory:      informerFactory,\n280: \t}, nil\n281: }\n282: \n283: // GetAgentRuntime retrieves the AgentRuntime resource\n284: func (k *K8sClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n285: \treturn k.agentRuntimeClient.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n286: }\n287: \n288: // UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus updates the status subresource\n289: func (k *K8sClient) UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n290: \treturn k.agentRuntimeClient.UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n291: }\n292: \n293: // GetCodeInterpreter retrieves the CodeInterpreter resource\n294: func (k *K8sClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n295: \treturn k.codeInterpreterClient.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n296: }\n297: \n298: // UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus updates the status subresource\n299: func (k *K8sClient) UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n300: \treturn k.codeInterpreterClient.UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n301: }\n302: \n303: // StartInformers starts the informers and waits for cache sync\n304: func (k *K8sClient) StartInformers() {\n305: \tk.informerFactory.Start(k.stopCh)\n306: }\n307: \n308: // WaitForCacheSync waits for informer caches to sync\n309: func (k *K8sClient) WaitForCacheSync() map[reflect.Type]bool {\n310: \treturn k.informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(k.stopCh)\n311: }\n312: \n313: // Stop stops the informers\n314: func (k *K8sClient) Stop() {\n315: \tclose(k.stopCh)\n316: }\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ### Workspace Manager\n320: \n321: **File**: `pkg/picod/workspace_manager.go`\n322: \n323: ```go\n324: // WorkspaceManager manages workspace lifecycle\n325: type WorkspaceManager struct {\n326: \tworkspaceDir     string\n327: \tk8sClient       *K8sClient\n328: \tmetrics         WorkspaceMetrics\n329: \tmetricsMutex    sync.RWMutex\n330: }\n331: \n332: // WorkspaceMetrics holds workspace statistics\n333: type WorkspaceMetrics struct {\n334: \tFileCount       int64     `json:\"file_count\"`\n335: \tTotalSize       int64     `json:\"total_size\"`\n336: \tLastModified    time.Time `json:\"last_modified\"`\n337: \tDirectoryCount  int64     `json:\"directory_count\"`\n338: }\n339: \n340: // NewWorkspaceManager creates a new workspace manager\n341: func NewWorkspaceManager(workspaceDir string, k8sClient *K8sClient) (*WorkspaceManager, error) {\n342: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(workspaceDir, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n343: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create workspace directory: %w\", err)\n344: \t}\n345: \n346: \treturn &WorkspaceManager{\n347: \t\tworkspaceDir: workspaceDir,\n348: \t\tk8sClient:   k8sClient,\n349: \t\tmetrics:     WorkspaceMetrics{},\n350: \t}, nil\n351: }\n352: \n353: // ProvisionWorkspace provisions a new workspace directory\n354: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) ProvisionWorkspace() error {\n355: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(wm.workspaceDir, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n356: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to provision workspace: %w\", err)\n357: \t}\n358: \treturn nil\n359: }\n360: \n361: // CleanupWorkspace cleans up the workspace directory\n362: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) CleanupWorkspace() error {\n363: \tif err := os.RemoveAll(wm.workspaceDir); err != nil {\n364: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to cleanup workspace: %w\", err)\n365: \t}\n366: \treturn nil\n367: }\n368: \n369: // UpdateMetrics updates workspace metrics\n370: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) UpdateMetrics() error {\n371: \tmetrics, err := wm.calculateMetrics()\n372: \tif err != nil {\n373: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to calculate workspace metrics: %w\", err)\n374: \t}\n375: \n376: \twm.metricsMutex.Lock()\n377: \twm.metrics = metrics\n378: \twm.metricsMutex.Unlock()\n379: \n380: \treturn nil\n381: }\n382: \n383: // calculateMetrics calculates workspace statistics\n384: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) calculateMetrics() (WorkspaceMetrics, error) {\n385: \tvar metrics WorkspaceMetrics\n386: \tvar totalSize int64\n387: \tvar fileCount, dirCount int64\n388: \tvar lastModified time.Time\n389: \n390: \terr := filepath.Walk(wm.workspaceDir, func(path string, info os.FileInfo, err error) error {\n391: \t\tif err != nil {\n392: \t\t\treturn err\n393: \t\t}\n394: \n395: \t\tif info.IsDir() {\n396: \t\t\tdirCount++\n397: \t\t} else {\n398: \t\t\tfileCount++\n399: \t\t\ttotalSize += info.Size()\n400: \t\t\tif info.ModTime().After(lastModified) {\n401: \t\t\t\tlastModified = info.ModTime()\n402: \t\t\t}\n403: \t\t}\n404: \n405: \t\treturn nil\n406: \t})\n407: \n408: \tif err != nil {\n409: \t\treturn WorkspaceMetrics{}, err\n410: \t}\n411: \n412: \tmetrics.FileCount = fileCount\n413: \tmetrics.TotalSize = totalSize\n414: \tmetrics.LastModified = lastModified\n415: \tmetrics.DirectoryCount = dirCount\n416: \n417: \treturn metrics, nil\n418: }\n419: \n420: // GetMetrics returns current workspace metrics\n421: func (wm *WorkspaceManager) GetMetrics() WorkspaceMetrics {\n422: \twm.metricsMutex.RLock()\n423: \tdefer wm.metricsMutex.RUnlock()\n424: \treturn wm.metrics\n425: }\n426: ```\n427: \n428: ### Status Reporter\n429: \n430: **File**: `pkg/picod/status_reporter.go`\n431: \n432: ```go\n433: // StatusReporter reports status to Kubernetes\n434: type StatusReporter struct {\n435: \tk8sClient       *K8sClient\n436: \tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\n437: \tagentRuntimeName string\n438: \tinterval        time.Duration\n439: \tstopCh          chan struct{}\n440: }\n441: \n442: // NewStatusReporter creates a new status reporter\n443: func NewStatusReporter(k8sClient *K8sClient, workspaceManager *WorkspaceManager, agentRuntimeName string, interval time.Duration) *StatusReporter {\n444: \treturn &StatusReporter{\n445: \t\tk8sClient:        k8sClient,\n446: \t\tworkspaceManager: workspaceManager,\n447: \t\tagentRuntimeName: agentRuntimeName,\n448: \t\tinterval:        interval,\n449: \t\tstopCh:          make(chan struct{}),\n450: \t}\n451: }\n452: \n453: // Start starts the status reporter\n454: func (sr *StatusReporter) Start() {\n455: \tticker := time.NewTicker(sr.interval)\n456: \tdefer ticker.Stop()\n457: \n458: \tfor {\n459: \t\tselect {\n460: \t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n461: \t\t\tif err := sr.reportStatus(); err != nil {\n462: \t\t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to report status: %v\", err)\n463: \t\t\t}\n464: \t\tcase <-sr.stopCh:\n465: \t\t\treturn\n466: \t\t}\n467: \t}\n468: }\n469: \n470: // Stop stops the status reporter\n471: func (sr *StatusReporter) Stop() {\n472: \tclose(sr.stopCh)\n473: }\n474: \n475: // reportStatus reports the current status to Kubernetes\n476: func (sr *StatusReporter) reportStatus() error {\n477: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 10*time.Second)\n478: \tdefer cancel()\n479: \n480: \tagentRuntime, err := sr.k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, sr.agentRuntimeName)\n481: \tif err != nil {\n482: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n483: \t}\n484: \n485: \tif err := sr.workspaceManager.UpdateMetrics(); err != nil {\n486: \t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to update workspace metrics: %v\", err)\n487: \t}\n488: \n489: \tmetrics := sr.workspaceManager.GetMetrics()\n490: \n491: \tagentRuntime.Status.Phase = \"Running\"\n492: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.FileCount = metrics.FileCount\n493: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.TotalSize = metrics.TotalSize\n494: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.LastModified = metav1.NewTime(metrics.LastModified)\n495: \tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.DirectoryCount = metrics.DirectoryCount\n496: \n497: \t_, err = sr.k8sClient.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime)\n498: \tif err != nil {\n499: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update AgentRuntime status: %w\", err)\n500: \t}\n501: \n502: \tklog.V(2).Infof(\"Successfully reported status for AgentRuntime %s\", sr.agentRuntimeName)\n503: \treturn nil\n504: }\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ### Informer Event Handlers\n508: \n509: **File**: `pkg/picod/informer.go`\n510: \n511: ```go\n512: // InformerManager manages informer event handlers\n513: type InformerManager struct {\n514: \tk8sClient         *K8sClient\n515: \tserver            *Server\n516: \tworkspaceManager  *WorkspaceManager\n517: }\n518: \n519: // NewInformerManager creates a new informer manager\n520: func NewInformerManager(k8sClient *K8sClient, server *Server, workspaceManager *WorkspaceManager) *InformerManager {\n521: \treturn &InformerManager{\n522: \t\tk8sClient:        k8sClient,\n523: \t\tserver:           server,\n524: \t\tworkspaceManager: workspaceManager,\n525: \t}\n526: }\n527: \n528: // SetupAgentRuntimeInformer sets up AgentRuntime informer\n529: func (im *InformerManager) SetupAgentRuntimeInformer() {\n530: \tinformer := im.k8sClient.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n531: \n532: \tinformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n533: \t\tAddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n534: \t\t\tagentRuntime := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n535: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s added\", agentRuntime.Name)\n536: \t\t},\n537: \t\tUpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n538: \t\t\toldAgentRuntime := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n539: \t\t\tnewAgentRuntime := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n540: \n541: \t\t\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(oldAgentRuntime.Spec, newAgentRuntime.Spec) {\n542: \t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s spec updated\", newAgentRuntime.Name)\n543: \t\t\t\tim.handleSpecUpdate(newAgentRuntime)\n544: \t\t\t}\n545: \t\t},\n546: \t\tDeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n547: \t\t\tagentRuntime := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n548: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s deleted, initiating shutdown\", agentRuntime.Name)\n549: \t\t\tim.handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(agentRuntime)\n550: \t\t},\n551: \t})\n552: }\n553: \n554: // SetupCodeInterpreterInformer sets up CodeInterpreter informer\n555: func (im *InformerManager) SetupCodeInterpreterInformer() {\n556: \tinformer := im.k8sClient.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n557: \n558: \tinformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n559: \t\tAddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n560: \t\t\tcodeInterpreter := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n561: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s added\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n562: \t\t},\n563: \t\tUpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n564: \t\t\toldCodeInterpreter := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n565: \t\t\tnewCodeInterpreter := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n566: \n567: \t\t\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(oldCodeInterpreter.Spec, newCodeInterpreter.Spec) {\n568: \t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s spec updated\", newCodeInterpreter.Name)\n569: \t\t\t\tim.handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(newCodeInterpreter)\n570: \t\t\t}\n571: \t\t},\n572: \t\tDeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n573: \t\t\tcodeInterpreter := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n574: \t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s deleted\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n575: \t\t},\n576: \t})\n577: }\n578: \n579: // handleSpecUpdate handles AgentRuntime spec updates\n580: func (im *InformerManager) handleSpecUpdate(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) {\n581: \tif agentRuntime.Spec.WorkspaceSize != nil {\n582: \t\tklog.Infof(\"Workspace size updated to %s\", *agentRuntime.Spec.WorkspaceSize)\n583: \t}\n584: \n585: \tif agentRuntime.Spec.TerminationGracePeriodSeconds != nil {\n586: \t\tklog.Infof(\"Termination grace period updated to %d\", *agentRuntime.Spec.TerminationGracePeriodSeconds)\n587: \t}\n588: }\n589: \n590: // handleAgentRuntimeDeletion handles AgentRuntime deletion\n591: func (im *InformerManager) handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) {\n592: \tif agentRuntime.Name == im.k8sClient.agentRuntimeName {\n593: \t\tklog.Info(\"This PicoD instance's AgentRuntime was deleted, initiating graceful shutdown\")\n594: \n595: \t\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n596: \t\tdefer cancel()\n597: \n598: \t\tif err := im.workspaceManager.CleanupWorkspace(); err != nil {\n599: \t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to cleanup workspace: %v\", err)\n600: \t\t}\n601: \n602: \t\tif err := im.server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n603: \t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to shutdown server: %v\", err)\n604: \t\t}\n605: \n606: \t\tos.Exit(0)\n607: \t}\n608: }\n609: \n610: // handleCodeInterpreterUpdate handles CodeInterpreter updates\n611: func (im *InformerManager) handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) {\n612: \tif codeInterpreter.Spec.RuntimeName == im.k8sClient.agentRuntimeName {\n613: \t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s for this runtime updated\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n614: \t}\n615: }\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### Server Integration\n619: \n620: **Modified File**: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n621: \n622: ```go\n623: type Server struct {\n624: \tengine           *gin.Engine\n625: \tconfig           Config\n626: \tauthManager      *AuthManager\n627: \tstartTime        time.Time\n628: \tworkspaceDir     string\n629: \thttpServer       *http.Server\n630: \tk8sClient        *K8sClient\n631: \tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\n632: \tstatusReporter   *StatusReporter\n633: \tinformerManager  *InformerManager\n634: }\n635: \n636: func NewServer(config Config) (*Server, error) {\n637: \tworkspace := config.Workspace\n638: \tif workspace == \"\" {\n639: \t\tcwd, err := os.Getwd()\n640: \t\tif err != nil {\n641: \t\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to get current working directory\", err.Error(), err)\n642: \t\t}\n643: \t\tworkspace = cwd\n644: \t}\n645: \n646: \tabsWorkspace, err := filepath.Abs(workspace)\n647: \tif err != nil {\n648: \t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to resolve workspace path\", err.Error(), err)\n649: \t}\n650: \n651: \tif err := os.MkdirAll(absWorkspace, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n652: \t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to create workspace directory\", err.Error(), err)\n653: \t}\n654: \n655: \tauthManager, err := NewAuthManager()\n656: \tif err != nil {\n657: \t\treturn nil, err\n658: \t}\n659: \n660: \tgin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n661: \tengine := gin.New()\n662: \tengine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n663: \tengine.Use(gin.Logger())\n664: \n665: \tserver := &Server{\n666: \t\tengine:       engine,\n667: \t\tconfig:       config,\n668: \t\tauthManager:  authManager,\n669: \t\tstartTime:    time.Now(),\n670: \t\tworkspaceDir: absWorkspace,\n671: \t}\n672: \n673: \tserver.registerRoutes()\n674: \n675: \tif config.K8sConfig != nil {\n676: \t\tk8sClient, err := NewK8sClient(*config.K8sConfig)\n677: \t\tif err != nil {\n678: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to create Kubernetes client: %v\", err)\n679: \t\t} else {\n680: \t\t\tserver.k8sClient = k8sClient\n681: \n682: \t\t\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(absWorkspace, k8sClient)\n683: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n684: \t\t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to create workspace manager: %v\", err)\n685: \t\t\t} else {\n686: \t\t\t\tserver.workspaceManager = workspaceManager\n687: \n688: \t\t\t\tif k8sClient.agentRuntimeName != \"\" {\n689: \t\t\t\t\tstatusReporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, k8sClient.agentRuntimeName, time.Minute)\n690: \t\t\t\t\tserver.statusReporter = statusReporter\n691: \t\t\t\t\tgo statusReporter.Start()\n692: \n693: \t\t\t\t\tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, server, workspaceManager)\n694: \t\t\t\t\tserver.informerManager = informerManager\n695: \t\t\t\t\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n696: \t\t\t\t\tinformerManager.SetupCodeInterpreterInformer()\n697: \n698: \t\t\t\t\tk8sClient.StartInformers()\n699: \t\t\t\t\tsynced := k8sClient.WaitForCacheSync()\n700: \t\t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"Informer cache sync: %v\", synced)\n701: \t\t\t\t}\n702: \t\t\t}\n703: \t\t}\n704: \t}\n705: \n706: \treturn server, nil\n707: }\n708: \n709: func (s *Server) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n710: \tklog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n711: \n712: \tif s.statusReporter != nil {\n713: \t\ts.statusReporter.Stop()\n714: \t}\n715: \n716: \tif s.k8sClient != nil {\n717: \t\ts.k8sClient.Stop()\n718: \t}\n719: \n720: \tif err := s.httpServer.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n721: \t\treturn err\n722: \t}\n723: \n724: \tklog.Info(\"Server shutdown complete\")\n725: \treturn nil\n726: }\n727: ```\n728: \n729: ### Configuration Extension\n730: \n731: **Modified File**: `pkg/picod/config.go`\n732: \n733: ```go\n734: type Config struct {\n735: \tPort      int          `json:\"port\"`\n736: \tWorkspace string       `json:\"workspace\"`\n737: \tK8sConfig *K8sConfig   `json:\"k8s_config,omitempty\"`\n738: }\n739: \n740: type K8sConfig struct {\n741: \tInCluster           bool   `json:\"in_cluster\"`\n742: \tKubeconfigPath      string `json:\"kubeconfig_path\"`\n743: \tNamespace           string `json:\"namespace\"`\n744: \tAgentRuntimeName    string `json:\"agent_runtime_name\"`\n745: \tAgentRuntimeNamespace string `json:\"agent_runtime_namespace\"`\n746: }\n747: ```\n748: \n749: ## API Contracts\n750: \n751: ### Existing HTTP APIs (Unchanged)\n752: \n753: All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged:\n754: \n755: - **POST /api/execute**: Execute commands in workspace\n756: - **POST /api/files**: Upload files to workspace (multipart or JSON Base64)\n757: - **GET /api/files**: List files in workspace directory\n758: - **GET /api/files/*path**: Download files from workspace\n759: - **GET /health**: Health check (no authentication)\n760: \n761: ### Kubernetes Resource Status\n762: \n763: The AgentRuntime status subresource is updated with workspace information:\n764: \n765: ```yaml\n766: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n767: kind: AgentRuntime\n768: metadata:\n769:   name: my-agent\n770:   namespace: default\n771: spec:\n772:   image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agent:latest\n773:   workspaceSize: \"1Gi\"\n774: status:\n775:   phase: \"Running\"\n776:   workspace:\n777:     fileCount: 42\n778:     totalSize: 1073741824\n779:     lastModified: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n780:     directoryCount: 8\n781:   conditions:\n782:     - type: \"Ready\"\n783:       status: \"True\"\n784:       lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n785:       reason: \"WorkspaceInitialized\"\n786:       message: \"Workspace initialized and ready\"\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ## Error Handling\n790: \n791: ### Kubernetes Integration Errors\n792: \n793: **File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go` (Extended)\n794: \n795: ```go\n796: const (\n797: \t// Kubernetes errors\n798: \tErrK8sConnectionFailed    = \"K8sConnectionFailed\"\n799: \tErrK8sResourceNotFound    = \"K8sResourceNotFound\"\n800: \tErrK8sUpdateFailed        = \"K8sUpdateFailed\"\n801: \tErrK8sInformerFailed      = \"K8sInformerFailed\"\n802: \tErrK8sConfigInvalid       = \"K8sConfigInvalid\"\n803: \n804: \t// Workspace errors\n805: \tErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed = \"WorkspaceProvisionFailed\"\n806: \tErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed   = \"WorkspaceCleanupFailed\"\n807: \tErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed   = \"WorkspaceMetricsFailed\"\n808: )\n809: \n810: var statusCodeMap = map[string]int{\n811: \t// Existing error codes...\n812: \tErrK8sConnectionFailed:      http.StatusServiceUnavailable,\n813: \tErrK8sResourceNotFound:      http.StatusNotFound,\n814: \tErrK8sUpdateFailed:          http.StatusInternalServerError,\n815: \tErrK8sInformerFailed:        http.StatusInternalServerError,\n816: \tErrK8sConfigInvalid:         http.StatusBadRequest,\n817: \tErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed: http.StatusInternalServerError,\n818: \tErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed:   http.StatusInternalServerError,\n819: \tErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed:   http.StatusInternalServerError,\n820: }\n821: ```\n822: \n823: ### Error Recovery Strategy\n824: \n825: 1. **Kubernetes Connection Failures**:\n826:    - Log error and continue in degraded mode (HTTP APIs still work)\n827:    - Retry connection with exponential backoff\n828:    - Mark Kubernetes integration as unavailable in health check\n829: \n830: 2. **Resource Update Failures**:\n831:    - Retry with backoff (up to 5 attempts)\n832:    - Log error and continue (non-critical)\n833:    - Queue status update for next reporting cycle\n834: \n835: 3. **Informer Failures**:\n836:    - Restart informer with backoff\n837:    - Log error and continue\n838:    - Health check indicates informer status\n839: \n840: 4. **Workspace Failures**:\n841:    - Log error and fail the operation\n842:    - Return HTTP 500 to client\n843:    - Update Kubernetes status with error condition\n844: \n845: ## Testing Strategy\n846: \n847: ### Unit Tests\n848: \n849: **File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n850: \n851: ```go\n852: func TestK8sClientCreation(t *testing.T) {\n853: \ttests := []struct {\n854: \t\tname        string\n855: \t\tconfig      K8sConfig\n856: \t\tsetupEnv    func()\n857: \t\tcleanupEnv  func()\n858: \t\twantErr     bool\n859: \t}{\n860: \t\t{\n861: \t\t\tname: \"in-cluster config\",\n862: \t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{\n863: \t\t\t\tInCluster: true,\n864: \t\t\t},\n865: \t\t\twantErr: false,\n866: \t\t},\n867: \t\t{\n868: \t\t\tname: \"kubeconfig path\",\n869: \t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{\n870: \t\t\t\tKubeconfigPath: \"/tmp/test-kubeconfig\",\n871: \t\t\t},\n872: \t\t\twantErr: false,\n873: \t\t},\n874: \t\t{\n875: \t\t\tname:   \"no config\",\n876: \t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{},\n877: \t\t\twantErr: true,\n878: \t\t},\n879: \t}\n880: \n881: \tfor _, tt := range tests {\n882: \t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n883: \t\t\tif tt.setupEnv != nil {\n884: \t\t\t\ttt.setupEnv()\n885: \t\t\t}\n886: \t\t\tif tt.cleanupEnv != nil {\n887: \t\t\t\tdefer tt.cleanupEnv()\n888: \t\t\t}\n889: \n890: \t\t\tclient, err := NewK8sClient(tt.config)\n891: \t\t\tif (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n892: \t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"NewK8sClient() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n893: \t\t\t}\n894: \n895: \t\t\tif !tt.wantErr && client != nil {\n896: \t\t\t\tif client.namespace == \"\" {\n897: \t\t\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected non-empty namespace\")\n898: \t\t\t\t}\n899: \t\t\t}\n900: \t\t})\n901: \t}\n902: }\n903: \n904: func TestK8sClientOperations(t *testing.T) {\n905: \tif testing.Short() {\n906: \t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test in short mode\")\n907: \t}\n908: \n909: \tclient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n910: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, client)\n911: \n912: \tctx := context.Background()\n913: \n914: \tt.Run(\"get non-existent resource\", func(t *testing.T) {\n915: \t\t_, err := client.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, \"non-existent\")\n916: \t\tif err == nil {\n917: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error for non-existent resource\")\n918: \t\t}\n919: \t})\n920: \n921: \tt.Run(\"update status\", func(t *testing.T) {\n922: \t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n923: \t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n924: \t\t\t\tName: \"test-agent\",\n925: \t\t\t},\n926: \t\t\tStatus: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n927: \t\t\t\tPhase: \"Running\",\n928: \t\t\t},\n929: \t\t}\n930: \n931: \t\t_, err := client.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime)\n932: \t\tif err == nil {\n933: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error for non-existent resource\")\n934: \t\t}\n935: \t})\n936: }\n937: ```\n938: \n939: **File**: `pkg/picod/workspace_manager_test.go`\n940: \n941: ```go\n942: func TestWorkspaceManager(t *testing.T) {\n943: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n944: \tk8sClient := &K8sClient{}\n945: \n946: \tmanager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n947: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n948: \n949: \tt.Run(\"provision workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n950: \t\terr := manager.ProvisionWorkspace()\n951: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n952: \n953: \t\tif _, err := os.Stat(workspace); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n954: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Workspace directory should exist\")\n955: \t\t}\n956: \t})\n957: \n958: \tt.Run(\"update metrics on empty workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n959: \t\terr := manager.UpdateMetrics()\n960: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n961: \n962: \t\tmetrics := manager.GetMetrics()\n963: \t\tif metrics.FileCount != 0 {\n964: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected 0 files, got %d\", metrics.FileCount)\n965: \t\t}\n966: \t})\n967: \n968: \tt.Run(\"update metrics with files\", func(t *testing.T) {\n969: \t\ttestFile := filepath.Join(workspace, \"test.txt\")\n970: \t\terr := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644)\n971: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n972: \n973: \t\terr = manager.UpdateMetrics()\n974: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n975: \n976: \t\tmetrics := manager.GetMetrics()\n977: \t\tif metrics.FileCount != 1 {\n978: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected 1 file, got %d\", metrics.FileCount)\n979: \t\t}\n980: \t\tif metrics.TotalSize != len(\"test content\") {\n981: \t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected size %d, got %d\", len(\"test content\"), metrics.TotalSize)\n982: \t\t}\n983: \t})\n984: \n985: \tt.Run(\"cleanup workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n986: \t\terr := manager.CleanupWorkspace()\n987: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n988: \n989: \t\tif _, err := os.Stat(workspace); !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n990: \t\t\tt.Error(\"Workspace directory should not exist after cleanup\")\n991: \t\t}\n992: \t})\n993: }\n994: ```\n995: \n996: **File**: `pkg/picod/status_reporter_test.go`\n997: \n998: ```go\n999: func TestStatusReporter(t *testing.T) {\n1000: \tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n1001: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n1002: \n1003: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1004: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1005: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1006: \n1007: \treporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent\", time.Second)\n1008: \n1009: \tt.Run(\"report status\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1010: \t\terr := reporter.reportStatus()\n1011: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1012: \t})\n1013: }\n1014: \n1015: func TestStatusReporterStart(t *testing.T) {\n1016: \tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n1017: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n1018: \n1019: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1020: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1021: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1022: \n1023: \treporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent\", 100*time.Millisecond)\n1024: \n1025: \tgo reporter.Start()\n1026: \n1027: \ttime.Sleep(300 * time.Millisecond)\n1028: \n1029: \treporter.Stop()\n1030: }\n1031: ```\n1032: \n1033: **File**: `pkg/picod/informer_test.go`\n1034: \n1035: ```go\n1036: func TestInformerManager(t *testing.T) {\n1037: \tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n1038: \tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n1039: \n1040: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1041: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1042: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1043: \n1044: \tserver := &Server{}\n1045: \tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, server, workspaceManager)\n1046: \n1047: \tt.Run(\"setup agent runtime informer\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1048: \t\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n1049: \t})\n1050: \n1051: \tt.Run(\"setup code interpreter informer\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1052: \t\tinformerManager.SetupCodeInterpreterInformer()\n1053: \t})\n1054: }\n1055: ```\n1056: \n1057: ### Integration Tests\n1058: \n1059: **File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n1060: \n1061: ```go\n1062: func TestK8sIntegrationFullWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n1063: \tif testing.Short() {\n1064: \t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test in short mode\")\n1065: \t}\n1066: \n1067: \tctx := context.Background()\n1068: \n1069: \tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n1070: \n1071: \tk8sConfig := K8sConfig{\n1072: \t\tInCluster:           false,\n1073: \t\tKubeconfigPath:      os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\"),\n1074: \t\tNamespace:           \"default\",\n1075: \t\tAgentRuntimeName:    \"test-agent-runtime\",\n1076: \t}\n1077: \n1078: \tk8sClient, err := NewK8sClient(k8sConfig)\n1079: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1080: \tdefer k8sClient.Stop()\n1081: \n1082: \tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n1083: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1084: \n1085: \tstatusReporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent-runtime\", time.Second)\n1086: \tgo statusReporter.Start()\n1087: \tdefer statusReporter.Stop()\n1088: \n1089: \tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, &Server{}, workspaceManager)\n1090: \tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n1091: \n1092: \tk8sClient.StartInformers()\n1093: \tsynced := k8sClient.WaitForCacheSync()\n1094: \trequire.True(t, synced.All())\n1095: \n1096: \tt.Run(\"workspace provisioning and metrics\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1097: \t\ttestFile := filepath.Join(workspace, \"test.txt\")\n1098: \t\terr := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644)\n1099: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1100: \n1101: \t\terr = workspaceManager.UpdateMetrics()\n1102: \t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n1103: \n1104: \t\tmetrics := workspaceManager.GetMetrics()\n1105: \t\trequire.Equal(t, int64(1), metrics.FileCount)\n1106: \t})\n1107: }\n1108: ```\n1109: \n1110: ## Dependencies\n1111: \n1112: ### Go Module Dependencies (Extended)\n1113: \n1114: ```go\n1115: require (\n1116:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n1117:     github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0\n1118:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n1119:     github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0\n1120:     k8s.io/client-go v0.30.3\n1121:     k8s.io/apimachinery v0.30.3\n1122:     k8s.io/api v0.30.3\n1123:     github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go v0.0.1\n1124: )\n1125: ```\n1126: \n1127: ### External Dependencies\n1128: \n1129: - **Gin Framework**: HTTP routing and middleware (existing)\n1130: - **JWT Library**: RSA-based JWT token validation (existing)\n1131: - **klog**: Structured logging (existing)\n1132: - **Kubernetes client-go**: Kubernetes API client (new)\n1133: - **AgentCube client-go**: Custom resource client (new)\n1134: - **Go Standard Library**: exec, os, filepath, time, context, crypto/rsa (existing)\n1135: \n1136: ## Security Considerations\n1137: \n1138: ### Authentication and Authorization\n1139: \n1140: - All HTTP APIs continue to require JWT authentication (unchanged)\n1141: - Kubernetes client uses in-cluster config or provided kubeconfig\n1142: - RBAC permissions required for PicoD service account:\n1143:   ```yaml\n1144:   apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1145:   kind: Role\n1146:   metadata:\n1147:     name: picod-role\n1148:   rules:\n1149:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1150:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n1151:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"updatestatus\"]\n1152:   ```\n1153: \n1154: ### Workspace Security\n1155: \n1156: - Path sanitization unchanged (existing security measures maintained)\n1157: - Workspace jail enforcement prevents directory traversal\n1158: - Symlink resolution and validation (existing)\n1159: - All file operations restricted to workspace directory\n1160: \n1161: ### Kubernetes Integration Security\n1162: \n1163: - PicoD only updates status subresource, cannot modify spec\n1164: - Limited RBAC permissions to prevent unauthorized modifications\n1165: - Service account tokens used for authentication\n1166: - No privileged access to cluster resources\n1167: \n1168: ### Error Message Security\n1169: \n1170: - Error messages do not expose sensitive Kubernetes information\n1171: - File paths in error messages remain relative to workspace\n1172: - Kubernetes errors logged but not exposed to HTTP clients\n1173: \n1174: ## Integration Points\n1175: \n1176: ### With AgentCube Platform\n1177: \n1178: PicoD integrates with AgentCube components through Kubernetes resources:\n1179: \n1180: - **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Creates AgentRuntime resources referencing PicoD instances\n1181: - **WorkloadManager**: Monitors AgentRuntime status for health and readiness\n1182: - **Session Store**: Queries AgentRuntime resources for workspace information\n1183: - **Controller**: Manages AgentRuntime lifecycle and configuration\n1184: \n1185: ### Deployment Integration\n1186: \n1187: ```yaml\n1188: apiVersion: v1\n1189: kind: Pod\n1190: metadata:\n1191:   name: picod-pod\n1192:   namespace: default\n1193: spec:\n1194:   serviceAccountName: picod\n1195:   containers:\n1196:   - name: picod\n1197:     image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n1198:     env:\n1199:     - name: PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER\n1200:       value: \"true\"\n1201:     - name: PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME\n1202:       valueFrom:\n1203:         fieldRef:\n1204:           fieldPath: metadata.annotations['agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime']\n1205:     - name: PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE\n1206:       valueFrom:\n1207:         fieldRef:\n1208:           fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n1209:     - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n1210:       valueFrom:\n1211:         secretKeyRef:\n1212:           name: picod-auth-keys\n1213:           key: public-key\n1214:     volumeMounts:\n1215:     - name: workspace\n1216:       mountPath: /workspace\n1217:   volumes:\n1218:   - name: workspace\n1219:     emptyDir:\n1220:       sizeLimit: 1Gi\n1221: ```\n1222: \n1223: ### Service Account\n1224: \n1225: ```yaml\n1226: apiVersion: v1\n1227: kind: ServiceAccount\n1228: metadata:\n1229:   name: picod\n1230: ---\n1231: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1232: kind: Role\n1233: metadata:\n1234:   name: picod-role\n1235: rules:\n1236: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1237:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n1238:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"updatestatus\"]\n1239: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1240:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n1241:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n1242: ---\n1243: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1244: kind: RoleBinding\n1245: metadata:\n1246:   name: picod-role-binding\n1247: subjects:\n1248: - kind: ServiceAccount\n1249:   name: picod\n1250: roleRef:\n1251:   kind: Role\n1252:   name: picod-role\n1253:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n1254: ```\n1255: \n1256: ## Configuration\n1257: \n1258: ### CLI Flags (Extended)\n1259: \n1260: | Flag                | Type   | Default | Description |\n1261: |---------------------|--------|---------|-------------|\n1262: | `-port`             | int    | 8080    | Port for the PicoD server to listen on |\n1263: | `-workspace`        | string | \"\"      | Root directory for file operations |\n1264: | `-k8s-in-cluster`   | bool   | false   | Use in-cluster Kubernetes config |\n1265: | `-k8s-kubeconfig`   | string | \"\"      | Path to kubeconfig file |\n1266: | `-k8s-namespace`    | string | \"\"      | Kubernetes namespace |\n1267: | `-k8s-agent-runtime`| string | \"\"      | AgentRuntime resource name |\n1268: \n1269: ### Environment Variables (Extended)\n1270: \n1271: | Name                          | Required | Description |\n1272: |-------------------------------|----------|-------------|\n1273: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`       | Yes      | PEM-encoded RSA public key for JWT validation |\n1274: | `PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER`        | No       | Set to \"true\" to use in-cluster config |\n1275: | `PICOD_K8S_KUBECONFIG`        | No       | Path to kubeconfig file |\n1276: | `PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE`         | No       | Kubernetes namespace |\n1277: | `PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME`| No       | AgentRuntime resource name |\n1278: \n1279: ### Configuration Example\n1280: \n1281: ```yaml\n1282: apiVersion: v1\n1283: kind: ConfigMap\n1284: metadata:\n1285:   name: picod-config\n1286: data:\n1287:   PORT: \"8080\"\n1288:   WORKSPACE: \"/workspace\"\n1289:   PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY: |\n1290:     -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n1291:     MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n1292:     -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n1293:   PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER: \"true\"\n1294:   PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME: \"my-agent-runtime\"\n1295: ```\n1296: \n1297: ## Documentation\n1298: \n1299: ### API Documentation\n1300: \n1301: All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged and documented in AR-015.\n1302: \n1303: ### Kubernetes Integration Documentation\n1304: \n1305: **Setup PicoD with Kubernetes Integration**:\n1306: ```bash\n1307: # Start PicoD with in-cluster config\n1308: ./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace -k8s-in-cluster -k8s-agent-runtime my-agent\n1309: \n1310: # Start PicoD with kubeconfig\n1311: ./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace -k8s-kubeconfig ~/.kube/config -k8s-agent-runtime my-agent -k8s-namespace default\n1312: ```\n1313: \n1314: **Monitoring AgentRuntime Status**:\n1315: ```bash\n1316: # Get AgentRuntime status\n1317: kubectl get agentruntime my-agent -o yaml\n1318: \n1319: # Watch AgentRuntime status updates\n1320: kubectl get agentruntime my-agent -w\n1321: \n1322: # Get workspace statistics from status\n1323: kubectl get agentruntime my-agent -o jsonpath='{.status.workspace}'\n1324: ```\n1325: \n1326: ### Usage Examples\n1327: \n1328: **Deploy PicoD with Kubernetes Integration**:\n1329: ```yaml\n1330: apiVersion: apps/v1\n1331: kind: Deployment\n1332: metadata:\n1333:   name: picod\n1334: spec:\n1335:   replicas: 1\n1336:   selector:\n1337:     matchLabels:\n1338:       app: picod\n1339:   template:\n1340:     metadata:\n1341:       labels:\n1342:         app: picod\n1343:       annotations:\n1344:         agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime: my-agent\n1345:     spec:\n1346:       serviceAccountName: picod\n1347:       containers:\n1348:       - name: picod\n1349:         image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n1350:         args:\n1351:         - -port=8080\n1352:         - -workspace=/workspace\n1353:         - -k8s-in-cluster\n1354:         env:\n1355:         - name: PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME\n1356:           valueFrom:\n1357:             fieldRef:\n1358:               fieldPath: metadata.annotations['agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime']\n1359:         - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n1360:           valueFrom:\n1361:             secretKeyRef:\n1362:               name: picod-auth-keys\n1363:               key: public-key\n1364:         volumeMounts:\n1365:         - name: workspace\n1366:           mountPath: /workspace\n1367:       volumes:\n1368:       - name: workspace\n1369:         emptyDir:\n1370:           sizeLimit: 1Gi\n1371: ```\n1372: \n1373: ## Success Criteria\n1374: \n1375: - [ ] HTTP file management APIs continue to work unchanged\n1376: - [ ] Kubernetes client successfully connects and authenticates\n1377: - [ ] AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources can be retrieved\n1378: - [ ] Status subresource updates succeed with workspace metrics\n1379: - [ ] Informers receive and handle resource events correctly\n1380: - [ ] Workspace manager provisions and cleans up workspaces\n1381: - [ ] Status reporter periodically updates Kubernetes resources\n1382: - [ ] Path sanitization and security remain effective\n1383: - [ ] Error handling covers Kubernetes integration failures\n1384: - [ ] Unit tests cover all new code paths\n1385: - [ ] Integration tests validate Kubernetes workflows\n1386: - [ ] RBAC permissions are correctly configured\n1387: - [ ] Graceful shutdown handles Kubernetes resource deletion\n1388: - [ ] Health check reflects Kubernetes integration status\n1389: - [ ] Documentation covers setup and usage patterns\n1390: \n1391: ## Migration Notes\n1392: \n1393: ### Backward Compatibility\n1394: \n1395: - All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged\n1396: - Kubernetes integration is optional (disabled by default)\n1397: - PicoD can run without Kubernetes client (degraded mode)\n1398: - No breaking changes to existing deployments\n1399: \n1400: ### Upgrading from AR-015\n1401: \n1402: To enable Kubernetes integration:\n1403: \n1404: 1. Update PicoD deployment to include service account\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1404. Use offset=1405 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n\n## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Extend PicoD file management capabilities with Kubernetes client-go integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through custom Kubernetes resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD file management API provides secure file operations within isolated workspace jails. AR-016 enhances this by integrating with Kubernetes through the generated client-go library, allowing PicoD instances to be managed as Kubernetes resources while maintaining existing HTTP-based file management APIs. This integration enables lifecycle management, health monitoring, and workspace orchestration at the Kubernetes level.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- Maintain existing HTTP-based file management APIs (upload, list, download)\n- Integrate with Kubernetes client-go for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- Support workspace provisioning and management through Kubernetes custom resources\n- Enable health status reporting to Kubernetes via status subresource\n- Provide watch/informer capabilities for real-time resource updates\n- Maintain workspace jail security and path sanitization","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-016/design.md","time":{"start":1775860779161,"end":1775860779182}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860779193,"sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","part":{"id":"prt_d798d087f001QBsZUd6RFTJDz5","messageID":"msg_d798cf694001lEh3lhRVWJr4gs","sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ed335b7d988445a398bbd9156d12829b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PicoD 命令执行 API Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Purpose**: Implement a secure HTTP daemon for command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail, providing JWT-protected APIs for code interpreter sandboxes in the AgentCube platform.\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs. It serves as the core execution engine for code interpreter sandboxes, enabling secure code execution, file operations (upload, list, download), and health monitoring with proper authentication.\n12: \n13: ### Key Requirements\n14: \n15: - HTTP server with configurable port and workspace directory\n16: - JWT (RSA) authentication for all API endpoints except health check\n17: - Command execution API with timeout support\n18: - File management APIs (upload, list, download)\n19: - Path security to enforce workspace jail\n20: - Support for multipart and JSON Base64 file uploads\n21: - Comprehensive error handling and logging\n22: - Zero-downtime deployment support with graceful shutdown\n23: \n24: ## Architecture\n25: \n26: ### Package Structure\n27: \n28: ```\n29: pkg/picod/\n30: ├── auth.go                # JWT authentication manager and middleware\n31: ├── execute.go             # Command execution handler\n32: ├── files.go               # File upload, list, download handlers\n33: ├── server.go              # Server initialization and configuration\n34: ├── handlers.go            # HTTP handler functions\n35: ├── middleware.go          # Custom middleware\n36: ├── errors.go              # Error types and handling\n37: ├── config.go              # Configuration structs\n38: └── constants.go           # Constants and defaults\n39: \n40: cmd/picod/\n41: ├── main.go                # CLI entry point\n42: └── flags.go               # CLI flag definitions\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### Component Interactions\n46: \n47: ```\n48: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                         PicoD HTTP Server                        │\n50: │                                                                  │\n51: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n52: │  │              Gin HTTP Engine                             │   │\n53: │  │  - Global middleware: Logger, Recovery                   │   │\n54: │  │  - API routes with JWT auth                              │   │\n55: │  │  - Health endpoint (no auth)                             │   │\n56: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n57: │                                                                  │\n58: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n59: │  │              Auth Manager                                │   │\n60: │  │  - JWT validation with RSA public key                    │   │\n61: │  │  - AuthMiddleware for /api/* routes                     │   │\n62: │  │  - Request body size limiting                            │   │\n63: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n64: │                                                                  │\n65: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n66: │  │              Request Handlers                            │   │\n67: │  │  - ExecuteHandler: Command execution                     │   │\n68: │  │  - UploadFileHandler: File upload                        │   │\n69: │  │  - ListFilesHandler: Directory listing                   │   │\n70: │  │  - DownloadFileHandler: File download                    │   │\n71: │  │  - HealthCheckHandler: Health status                     │   │\n72: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n73: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n74:            │                     │                     │\n75:            │                     │                     │\n76:            ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n77:  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n78:  │  File System     │  │     OS Exec      │  │     JWT Keys     │\n79:  │  (Workspace Jail)│  │  (Commands)      │  │  (Auth)          │\n80:  │  - Files         │  │  - Contexts      │  │  - RSA Public    │\n81:  │  - Directories   │  │  - Timeouts      │  │  - Validation    │\n82:  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Request Flow\n86: \n87: ```\n88: HTTP Request\n89:     ↓\n90: [Global Middleware] Logger, Recovery\n91:     ↓\n92: [Route Matching] Check endpoint\n93:     ↓\n94: [Auth Middleware?] If /api/* path:\n95:     ↓ Yes                      ↓ No (/health)\n96: [JWT Validation]              [Process Request]\n97:     - Parse Authorization        - Health check\n98:     - Verify RSA signature\n99:     - Check expiration\n100:     ↓\n101: [Body Size Limit] MaxBytesReader (32 MiB)\n102:     ↓\n103: [Handler Processing]\n104:     - Path sanitization\n105:     - Request validation\n106:     - Business logic\n107:     - Error handling\n108:     ↓\n109: [Response]\n110:     - JSON response\n111:     - Proper headers\n112:     - Error format\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Command Execution Flow\n116: \n117: ```\n118: POST /api/execute\n119:     ↓\n120: [JWT Validation] Verify token\n121:     ↓\n122: [Request Binding] Parse ExecuteRequest JSON\n123:     ↓\n124: [Validation] Check command non-empty\n125:     ↓\n126: [Timeout Parsing] Parse timeout or use default (60s)\n127:     ↓\n128: [Working Dir] Sanitize and resolve path\n129:     ↓\n130: [Environment] Merge process and request env vars\n131:     ↓\n132: [Command Setup] Create exec.CommandContext\n133:     ↓\n134: [Execution] Run command with context\n135:     ↓\n136: [Output Capture] Capture stdout and stderr\n137:     ↓\n138: [Result] Determine exit code\n139:     - Timeout: 124\n140:     - Success: 0\n141:     - Error: actual exit code\n142:     ↓\n143: [Response] Return ExecuteResponse JSON\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ## Data Structures\n147: \n148: ### Server Configuration\n149: \n150: **File**: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n151: \n152: ```go\n153: // Config represents the server configuration\n154: type Config struct {\n155:     Port      int    `json:\"port\"`\n156:     Workspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n157: }\n158: \n159: // Server represents the PicoD HTTP server\n160: type Server struct {\n161:     engine      *gin.Engine\n162:     config      Config\n163:     authManager *AuthManager\n164:     startTime   time.Time\n165:     workspaceDir string\n166: }\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### Authentication\n170: \n171: **File**: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n172: \n173: ```go\n174: // AuthManager manages JWT authentication\n175: type AuthManager struct {\n176:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n177:     mutex     sync.RWMutex\n178: }\n179: \n180: // AuthClaims represents JWT claims\n181: type AuthClaims struct {\n182:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n183:     // Additional custom claims can be added here\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Command Execution\n188: \n189: **File**: `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n190: \n191: ```go\n192: // ExecuteRequest represents a command execution request\n193: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n194:     Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n195:     Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n196:     WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n197:     Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n198: }\n199: \n200: // ExecuteResponse represents the command execution result\n201: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n202:     Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n203:     Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n204:     ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n205:     Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n206:     StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n207:     EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n208: }\n209: \n210: // ExecutionResult represents the internal execution result\n211: type ExecutionResult struct {\n212:     Stdout    []byte\n213:     Stderr    []byte\n214:     ExitCode  int\n215:     StartTime time.Time\n216:     EndTime   time.Time\n217:     Duration  time.Duration\n218: }\n219: ```\n220: \n221: ### File Operations\n222: \n223: **File**: `pkg/picod/files.go`\n224: \n225: ```go\n226: // FileInfo represents file information\n227: type FileInfo struct {\n228:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n229:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n230:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n231:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n232: }\n233: \n234: // UploadFileRequest represents a file upload request (JSON format)\n235: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n236:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n237:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n238:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n239: }\n240: \n241: // FileEntry represents a file or directory entry\n242: type FileEntry struct {\n243:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n244:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n245:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n246:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n247:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n248: }\n249: \n250: // ListFilesResponse represents a directory listing response\n251: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n252:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n253: }\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### Error Responses\n257: \n258: **File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: // ErrorResponse represents a standard error response\n262: type ErrorResponse struct {\n263:     Error  string `json:\"error\"`\n264:     Code   int    `json:\"code\"`\n265:     Detail string `json:\"detail,omitempty\"`\n266: }\n267: \n268: // Error codes\n269: const (\n270:     ErrorCodeBadRequest    = \"BadRequest\"\n271:     ErrorCodeUnauthorized  = \"Unauthorized\"\n272:     ErrorCodeNotFound      = \"NotFound\"\n273:     ErrorCodeInternalError = \"InternalError\"\n274: )\n275: \n276: // PicoDError represents a PicoD-specific error\n277: type PicoDError struct {\n278:     Code    string\n279:     Message string\n280:     Detail  string\n281:     Err     error\n282: }\n283: \n284: // Error implements the error interface\n285: func (e *PicoDError) Error() string {\n286:     if e.Err != nil {\n287:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (caused by: %v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Err)\n288:     }\n289:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n290: }\n291: \n292: // Unwrap returns the underlying error\n293: func (e *PicoDError) Unwrap() error {\n294:     return e.Err\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ## API Contracts\n299: \n300: ### Command Execution API\n301: \n302: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/execute`\n303: \n304: **Headers**:\n305: ```\n306: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>\n307: Content-Type: application/json\n308: ```\n309: \n310: **Request Body**:\n311: ```json\n312: {\n313:   \"command\": [\"python\", \"script.py\"],\n314:   \"timeout\": \"30s\",\n315:   \"working_dir\": \"workspace\",\n316:   \"env\": {\n317:     \"VAR1\": \"value1\"\n318:   }\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: **Response (Success - HTTP 200)**:\n323: ```json\n324: {\n325:   \"stdout\": \"command output\",\n326:   \"stderr\": \"error output\",\n327:   \"exit_code\": 0,\n328:   \"duration\": 1.234,\n329:   \"start_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n330:   \"end_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:01Z\"\n331: }\n332: ```\n333: \n334: **Response (Error - HTTP 400)**:\n335: ```json\n336: {\n337:   \"error\": \"command cannot be empty\",\n338:   \"code\": 400\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Response (Authentication Error - HTTP 401)**:\n343: ```json\n344: {\n345:   \"error\": \"Invalid token\",\n346:   \"code\": 401,\n347:   \"detail\": \"token expired\"\n348: }\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ### File Upload API\n352: \n353: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n354: \n355: **Headers** (Multipart):\n356: ```\n357: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>\n358: Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary\n359: ```\n360: \n361: **Request Body** (Multipart):\n362: ```\n363: ------WebKitFormBoundary\n364: Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"path\"\n365: workspace/file.txt\n366: ------WebKitFormBoundary\n367: Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"file\"; filename=\"file.txt\"\n368: Content-Type: text/plain\n369: \n370: File content here\n371: ------WebKitFormBoundary--\n372: ```\n373: \n374: **Request Body** (JSON Base64):\n375: ```json\n376: {\n377:   \"path\": \"workspace/file.txt\",\n378:   \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gd29ybGQh\",\n379:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n380: }\n381: ```\n382: \n383: **Response (Success - HTTP 200)**:\n384: ```json\n385: {\n386:   \"path\": \"workspace/file.txt\",\n387:   \"size\": 1024,\n388:   \"mode\": \"0644\",\n389:   \"modified\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n390: }\n391: ```\n392: \n393: ### File List API\n394: \n395: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files?path=<directory>`\n396: \n397: **Headers**:\n398: ```\n399: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>\n400: ```\n401: \n402: **Response (Success - HTTP 200)**:\n403: ```json\n404: {\n405:   \"files\": [\n406:     {\n407:       \"name\": \"file.txt\",\n408:       \"size\": 1024,\n409:       \"modified\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n410:       \"mode\": \"0644\",\n411:       \"is_dir\": false\n412:     }\n413:   ]\n414: }\n415: ```\n416: \n417: **Response (Error - HTTP 404)**:\n418: ```json\n419: {\n420:   \"error\": \"Directory not found\",\n421:   \"code\": 404\n422: }\n423: ```\n424: \n425: ### File Download API\n426: \n427: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files/<path>`\n428: \n429: **Headers**:\n430: ```\n431: Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>\n432: ```\n433: \n434: **Response (Success - HTTP 200)**:\n435: ```\n436: Content-Description: File Transfer\n437: Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary\n438: Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\"file.txt\"\n439: Content-Type: text/plain\n440: \n441: File content here\n442: ```\n443: \n444: **Response (Error - HTTP 404)**:\n445: ```json\n446: {\n447:   \"error\": \"File not found\",\n448:   \"code\": 404\n449: }\n450: ```\n451: \n452: ### Health Check API\n453: \n454: **Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n455: \n456: **Headers**: None (no authentication required)\n457: \n458: **Response (Success - HTTP 200)**:\n459: ```json\n460: {\n461:   \"status\": \"ok\",\n462:   \"service\": \"PicoD\",\n463:   \"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n464:   \"uptime\": \"1h30m45s\"\n465: }\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ## Error Handling\n469: \n470: ### Error Types\n471: \n472: **File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n473: \n474: ```go\n475: // Error types\n476: const (\n477:     // Validation errors\n478:     ErrInvalidCommand       = \"InvalidCommand\"\n479:     ErrEmptyCommand         = \"EmptyCommand\"\n480:     ErrInvalidTimeout       = \"InvalidTimeout\"\n481:     ErrInvalidWorkingDir    = \"InvalidWorkingDir\"\n482:     ErrInvalidBase64        = \"InvalidBase64\"\n483:     ErrMissingPath          = \"MissingPath\"\n484:     \n485:     // File system errors\n486:     ErrFileNotFound         = \"FileNotFound\"\n487:     ErrDirectoryNotFound    = \"DirectoryNotFound\"\n488:     ErrPathIsDirectory      = \"PathIsDirectory\"\n489:     ErrAccessDenied         = \"AccessDenied\"\n490:     \n491:     // Authentication errors\n492:     ErrMissingAuthHeader    = \"MissingAuthHeader\"\n493:     ErrInvalidAuthFormat    = \"InvalidAuthFormat\"\n494:     ErrInvalidToken         = \"InvalidToken\"\n495:     ErrInvalidSignature     = \"InvalidSignature\"\n496:     ErrTokenExpired         = \"TokenExpired\"\n497:     ErrInvalidPublicKey     = \"InvalidPublicKey\"\n498:     \n499:     // Server errors\n500:     ErrServerInternal       = \"ServerInternal\"\n501:     ErrWorkspaceNotInit     = \"WorkspaceNotInit\"\n502: )\n503: \n504: // HTTP status code mapping\n505: var statusCodeMap = map[string]int{\n506:     ErrInvalidCommand:      http.StatusBadRequest,\n507:     ErrEmptyCommand:        http.StatusBadRequest,\n508:     ErrInvalidTimeout:      http.StatusBadRequest,\n509:     ErrInvalidWorkingDir:   http.StatusBadRequest,\n510:     ErrInvalidBase64:       http.StatusBadRequest,\n511:     ErrMissingPath:         http.StatusBadRequest,\n512:     ErrFileNotFound:        http.StatusNotFound,\n513:     ErrDirectoryNotFound:   http.StatusNotFound,\n514:     ErrPathIsDirectory:     http.StatusBadRequest,\n515:     ErrAccessDenied:        http.StatusBadRequest,\n516:     ErrMissingAuthHeader:   http.StatusUnauthorized,\n517:     ErrInvalidAuthFormat:   http.StatusUnauthorized,\n518:     ErrInvalidToken:        http.StatusUnauthorized,\n519:     ErrInvalidSignature:    http.StatusUnauthorized,\n520:     ErrTokenExpired:        http.StatusUnauthorized,\n521:     ErrInvalidPublicKey:    http.StatusInternalServerError,\n522:     ErrServerInternal:      http.StatusInternalServerError,\n523:     ErrWorkspaceNotInit:    http.StatusInternalServerError,\n524: }\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ### Error Handling Strategy\n528: \n529: ```go\n530: // HandleError handles errors and returns appropriate HTTP responses\n531: func HandleError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n532:     status := http.StatusInternalServerError\n533:     code := ErrorCodeInternalError\n534:     message := err.Error()\n535:     detail := \"\"\n536:     \n537:     if picoDErr, ok := err.(*PicoDError); ok {\n538:         code = picoDErr.Code\n539:         message = picoDErr.Message\n540:         detail = picoDErr.Detail\n541:         if mappedStatus, exists := statusCodeMap[code]; exists {\n542:             status = mappedStatus\n543:         }\n544:     }\n545:     \n546:     c.JSON(status, ErrorResponse{\n547:         Error:  message,\n548:         Code:   status,\n549:         Detail: detail,\n550:     })\n551: }\n552: \n553: // NewError creates a new PicoD error\n554: func NewError(code, message, detail string, err error) *PicoDError {\n555:     return &PicoDError{\n556:         Code:    code,\n557:         Message: message,\n558:         Detail:  detail,\n559:         Err:     err,\n560:     }\n561: }\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ## Constants\n565: \n566: **File**: `pkg/picod/constants.go`\n567: \n568: ```go\n569: // Environment variables\n570: const (\n571:     PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n572: )\n573: \n574: // Exit codes\n575: const (\n576:     TimeoutExitCode = 124\n577: )\n578: \n579: // Size limits\n580: const (\n581:     MaxBodySize    = 32 << 20 // 32 MiB\n582: )\n583: \n584: // Default values\n585: const (\n586:     DefaultPort         = 8080\n587:     DefaultTimeout      = 60 * time.Second\n588:     DefaultFileMode     = 0644\n589:     DefaultDirMode      = 0755\n590:     MaxFileMode         = 0777\n591:     ReadHeaderTimeout   = 10 * time.Second\n592: )\n593: \n594: // Version\n595: const (\n596:     ServiceName = \"PicoD\"\n597:     Version     = \"0.0.1\"\n598: )\n599: \n600: // HTTP headers\n601: const (\n602:     HeaderAuthorization      = \"Authorization\"\n603:     HeaderContentDescription = \"Content-Description\"\n604:     HeaderContentDisposition = \"Content-Disposition\"\n605:     HeaderContentEncoding    = \"Content-Transfer-Encoding\"\n606:     HeaderContentType        = \"Content-Type\"\n607: )\n608: \n609: // MIME types\n610: const (\n611:     MIMEOctetStream = \"application/octet-stream\"\n612:     MIMEMultipart   = \"multipart/form-data\"\n613: )\n614: \n615: // Error messages\n616: const (\n617:     ErrMsgMissingAuthHeader    = \"Missing Authorization header\"\n618:     ErrMsgInvalidAuthFormat    = \"Use Bearer <token> format\"\n619:     ErrMsgInvalidToken         = \"Invalid token\"\n620:     ErrMsgEmptyCommand         = \"command cannot be empty\"\n621:     ErrMsgMissingPathParam     = \"Missing 'path' query parameter\"\n622:     ErrMsgDirectoryNotFound    = \"Directory not found\"\n623:     ErrMsgFileNotFound         = \"File not found\"\n624:     ErrMsgPathIsDirectory      = \"Path is a directory, not a file\"\n625:     ErrMsgAccessDenied         = \"Access denied: path escapes workspace\"\n626:     ErrMsgInvalidWorkingDir    = \"Invalid working directory: \"\n627:     ErrMsgWorkspaceNotInit     = \"workspace directory not initialized\"\n628:     ErrMsgInvalidBase64        = \"invalid base64 encoding\"\n629: )\n630: ```\n631: \n632: ## Path Security\n633: \n634: **File**: `pkg/picod/files.go`\n635: \n636: ```go\n637: // sanitizePath sanitizes a path to ensure it stays within the workspace\n638: func (s *Server) sanitizePath(path string) (string, error) {\n639:     if s.workspaceDir == \"\" {\n640:         return \"\", NewError(ErrWorkspaceNotInit, ErrMsgWorkspaceNotInit, \"\", nil)\n641:     }\n642:     \n643:     // Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks)\n644:     resolvedWorkspace, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(s.workspaceDir)\n645:     if err != nil {\n646:         resolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(s.workspaceDir)\n647:     }\n648:     resolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(resolvedWorkspace)\n649:     \n650:     // Clean the input path\n651:     cleanPath := filepath.Clean(path)\n652:     \n653:     // If absolute path, strip leading separator\n654:     if filepath.IsAbs(cleanPath) {\n655:         cleanPath = strings.TrimPrefix(cleanPath, string(os.PathSeparator))\n656:     }\n657:     \n658:     // Join with workspace and clean\n659:     fullPath := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))\n660:     \n661:     // Check if path is relative to workspace\n662:     relPath, err := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, fullPath)\n663:     if err != nil {\n664:         return \"\", NewError(ErrAccessDenied, ErrMsgAccessDenied, err.Error(), err)\n665:     }\n666:     \n667:     // Check for path traversal attempts\n668:     if strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+string(os.PathSeparator)) || relPath == \"..\" {\n669:         return \"\", NewError(ErrAccessDenied, ErrMsgAccessDenied, \"\", nil)\n670:     }\n671:     \n672:     // Resolve symlinks in the target path\n673:     resolvedPath, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPath)\n674:     if err == nil {\n675:         // Re-check if resolved path is still within workspace\n676:         resolvedRelPath, err := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, resolvedPath)\n677:         if err != nil || strings.HasPrefix(resolvedRelPath, \"..\"+string(os.PathSeparator)) {\n678:             return \"\", NewError(ErrAccessDenied, ErrMsgAccessDenied, \"\", nil)\n679:         }\n680:         return resolvedPath, nil\n681:     }\n682:     \n683:     // Path doesn't exist yet, return the validated path\n684:     return fullPath, nil\n685: }\n686: \n687: // parseFileMode parses a file mode string to os.FileMode\n688: func parseFileMode(modeStr string) os.FileMode {\n689:     if modeStr == \"\" {\n690:         return DefaultFileMode\n691:     }\n692:     \n693:     mode, err := strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)\n694:     if err != nil {\n695:         return DefaultFileMode\n696:     }\n697:     \n698:     if mode > MaxFileMode {\n699:         return DefaultFileMode\n700:     }\n701:     \n702:     return os.FileMode(mode)\n703: }\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ## Testing Strategy\n707: \n708: ### Unit Tests\n709: \n710: **File**: `pkg/picod/server_test.go`\n711: \n712: ```go\n713: func TestServerInitialization(t *testing.T) {\n714:     tests := []struct {\n715:         name        string\n716:         config      Config\n717:         wantErr     bool\n718:         setupEnv    func()\n719:         cleanupEnv  func()\n720:     }{\n721:         {\n722:             name: \"default configuration\",\n723:             config: Config{\n724:                 Port: DefaultPort,\n725:                 Workspace: \"\",\n726:             },\n727:             wantErr: false,\n728:             setupEnv: func() {\n729:                 os.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, testPublicKey)\n730:             },\n731:             cleanupEnv: func() {\n732:                 os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n733:             },\n734:         },\n735:         {\n736:             name: \"custom configuration\",\n737:             config: Config{\n738:                 Port: 9090,\n739:                 Workspace: \"/tmp/test-workspace\",\n740:             },\n741:             wantErr: false,\n742:             setupEnv: func() {\n743:                 os.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, testPublicKey)\n744:             },\n745:             cleanupEnv: func() {\n746:                 os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n747:             },\n748:         },\n749:     }\n750:     \n751:     for _, tt := range tests {\n752:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n753:             tt.setupEnv()\n754:             defer tt.cleanupEnv()\n755:             \n756:             server, err := NewServer(tt.config)\n757:             if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n758:                 t.Errorf(\"NewServer() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n759:             }\n760:             \n761:             if !tt.wantErr {\n762:                 if server == nil {\n763:                     t.Fatal(\"Expected non-nil server\")\n764:                 }\n765:                 if server.config.Port != tt.config.Port {\n766:                     t.Errorf(\"Expected port %d, got %d\", tt.config.Port, server.config.Port)\n767:                 }\n768:             }\n769:         })\n770:     }\n771: }\n772: ```\n773: \n774: **File**: `pkg/picod/execute_test.go`\n775: \n776: ```go\n777: func TestExecuteHandler(t *testing.T) {\n778:     // Setup test server\n779:     server := setupTestServer(t)\n780:     defer cleanupTestServer(t, server)\n781:     \n782:     // Create test JWT token\n783:     token := createTestToken(t)\n784:     \n785:     tests := []struct {\n786:         name           string\n787:         request        ExecuteRequest\n788:         wantStatusCode int\n789:         wantExitCode   int\n790:     }{\n791:         {\n792:             name: \"successful execution\",\n793:             request: ExecuteRequest{\n794:                 Command: []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"},\n795:                 Timeout: \"\",\n796:             },\n797:             wantStatusCode: http.StatusOK,\n798:             wantExitCode:   0,\n799:         },\n800:         {\n801:             name: \"empty command\",\n802:             request: ExecuteRequest{\n803:                 Command: []string{},\n804:                 Timeout: \"\",\n805:             },\n806:             wantStatusCode: http.StatusBadRequest,\n807:             wantExitCode:   -1,\n808:         },\n809:         {\n810:             name: \"invalid timeout\",\n811:             request: ExecuteRequest{\n812:                 Command: []string{\"echo\", \"hello\"},\n813:                 Timeout: \"invalid\",\n814:             },\n815:             wantStatusCode: http.StatusBadRequest,\n816:             wantExitCode:   -1,\n817:         },\n818:     }\n819:     \n820:     for _, tt := range tests {\n821:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n822:             body, _ := json.Marshal(tt.request)\n823:             req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/api/execute\", bytes.NewBuffer(body))\n824:             req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n825:             req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n826:             \n827:             w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n828:             server.engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n829:             \n830:             if w.Code != tt.wantStatusCode {\n831:                 t.Errorf(\"Expected status %d, got %d\", tt.wantStatusCode, w.Code)\n832:             }\n833:             \n834:             if tt.wantStatusCode == http.StatusOK {\n835:                 var response ExecuteResponse\n836:                 json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &response)\n837:                 if response.ExitCode != tt.wantExitCode {\n838:                     t.Errorf(\"Expected exit code %d, got %d\", tt.wantExitCode, response.ExitCode)\n839:                 }\n840:             }\n841:         })\n842:     }\n843: }\n844: ```\n845: \n846: **File**: `pkg/picod/files_test.go`\n847: \n848: ```go\n849: func TestFileOperations(t *testing.T) {\n850:     // Setup test server and workspace\n851:     workspace := t.TempDir()\n852:     server := setupTestServerWithWorkspace(t, workspace)\n853:     defer cleanupTestServer(t, server)\n854:     \n855:     token := createTestToken(t)\n856:     \n857:     t.Run(\"upload file\", func(t *testing.T) {\n858:         content := base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString([]byte(\"test content\"))\n859:         request := UploadFileRequest{\n860:             Path:    \"test.txt\",\n861:             Content: content,\n862:             Mode:    \"0644\",\n863:         }\n864:         \n865:         body, _ := json.Marshal(request)\n866:         req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/api/files\", bytes.NewBuffer(body))\n867:         req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n868:         req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n869:         \n870:         w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n871:         server.engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n872:         \n873:         if w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n874:             t.Errorf(\"Expected status 200, got %d\", w.Code)\n875:         }\n876:     })\n877:     \n878:     t.Run(\"list files\", func(t *testing.T) {\n879:         req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/api/files?path=.\", nil)\n880:         req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n881:         \n882:         w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n883:         server.engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n884:         \n885:         if w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n886:             t.Errorf(\"Expected status 200, got %d\", w.Code)\n887:         }\n888:         \n889:         var response ListFilesResponse\n890:         json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &response)\n891:         if len(response.Files) == 0 {\n892:             t.Error(\"Expected files in listing\")\n893:         }\n894:     })\n895:     \n896:     t.Run(\"download file\", func(t *testing.T) {\n897:         req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/api/files/test.txt\", nil)\n898:         req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n899:         \n900:         w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n901:         server.engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n902:         \n903:         if w.Code != http.StatusOK {\n904:             t.Errorf(\"Expected status 200, got %d\", w.Code)\n905:         }\n906:         \n907:         if w.Body.String() != \"test content\" {\n908:             t.Errorf(\"Expected 'test content', got '%s'\", w.Body.String())\n909:         }\n910:     })\n911: }\n912: ```\n913: \n914: **File**: `pkg/picod/auth_test.go`\n915: \n916: ```go\n917: func TestAuthMiddleware(t *testing.T) {\n918:     server := setupTestServer(t)\n919:     defer cleanupTestServer(t, server)\n920:     \n921:     tests := []struct {\n922:         name           string\n923:         setupRequest   func(*http.Request)\n924:         wantStatusCode int\n925:         wantError      string\n926:     }{\n927:         {\n928:             name: \"missing authorization header\",\n929:             setupRequest: func(req *http.Request) {\n930:                 // No authorization header\n931:             },\n932:             wantStatusCode: http.StatusUnauthorized,\n933:             wantError:      ErrMsgMissingAuthHeader,\n934:         },\n935:         {\n936:             name: \"invalid authorization format\",\n937:             setupRequest: func(req *http.Request) {\n938:                 req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"InvalidFormat token\")\n939:             },\n940:             wantStatusCode: http.StatusUnauthorized,\n941:             wantError:      ErrMsgInvalidAuthFormat,\n942:         },\n943:         {\n944:             name: \"valid token\",\n945:             setupRequest: func(req *http.Request) {\n946:                 token := createTestToken(t)\n947:                 req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n948:             },\n949:             wantStatusCode: http.StatusOK,\n950:             wantError:      \"\",\n951:         },\n952:     }\n953:     \n954:     for _, tt := range tests {\n955:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n956:             req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/api/execute\", bytes.NewBuffer([]byte(`{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"test\"]}`)))\n957:             tt.setupRequest(req)\n958:             req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n959:             \n960:             w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n961:             server.engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n962:             \n963:             if w.Code != tt.wantStatusCode {\n964:                 t.Errorf(\"Expected status %d, got %d\", tt.wantStatusCode, w.Code)\n965:             }\n966:         })\n967:     }\n968: }\n969: ```\n970: \n971: ### Integration Tests\n972: \n973: **File**: `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n974: \n975: ```go\n976: func TestServerIntegration(t *testing.T) {\n977:     // Create temporary workspace\n978:     workspace := t.TempDir()\n979:     \n980:     // Setup environment\n981:     os.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, testPublicKey)\n982:     defer os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n983:     \n984:     // Create server\n985:     config := Config{\n986:         Port:      testPort,\n987:         Workspace: workspace,\n988:     }\n989:     server, err := NewServer(config)\n990:     require.NoError(t, err)\n991:     \n992:     // Start server in goroutine\n993:     go func() {\n994:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil && !errors.Is(err, http.ErrServerClosed) {\n995:             t.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n996:         }\n997:     }()\n998:     \n999:     // Wait for server to be ready\n1000:     time.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n1001:     \n1002:     // Cleanup\n1003:     defer func() {\n1004:         ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n1005:         defer cancel()\n1006:         server.Shutdown(ctx)\n1007:     }()\n1008:     \n1009:     // Run integration tests\n1010:     t.Run(\"full workflow\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1011:         token := createTestToken(t)\n1012:         \n1013:         // 1. Health check\n1014:         resp := doRequest(t, \"GET\", \"http://localhost:\"+strconv.Itoa(testPort)+\"/health\", nil, \"\")\n1015:         require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n1016:         \n1017:         // 2. Upload file\n1018:         uploadReq := UploadFileRequest{\n1019:             Path:    \"test.py\",\n1020:             Content: base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString([]byte(\"print('hello')\")),\n1021:             Mode:    \"0644\",\n1022:         }\n1023:         uploadBody, _ := json.Marshal(uploadReq)\n1024:         resp = doRequest(t, \"POST\", \"http://localhost:\"+strconv.Itoa(testPort)+\"/api/files\", uploadBody, token)\n1025:         require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n1026:         \n1027:         // 3. Execute command\n1028:         execReq := ExecuteRequest{\n1029:             Command: []string{\"python\", \"test.py\"},\n1030:             Timeout: \"10s\",\n1031:         }\n1032:         execBody, _ := json.Marshal(execReq)\n1033:         resp = doRequest(t, \"POST\", \"http://localhost:\"+strconv.Itoa(testPort)+\"/api/execute\", execBody, token)\n1034:         require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n1035:         \n1036:         var execResp ExecuteResponse\n1037:         json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&execResp)\n1038:         require.Equal(t, 0, execResp.ExitCode)\n1039:         require.Contains(t, execResp.Stdout, \"hello\")\n1040:         \n1041:         // 4. List files\n1042:         resp = doRequest(t, \"GET\", \"http://localhost:\"+strconv.Itoa(testPort)+\"/api/files?path=.\", nil, token)\n1043:         require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n1044:         \n1045:         var listResp ListFilesResponse\n1046:         json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&listResp)\n1047:         require.Len(t, listResp.Files, 1)\n1048:         require.Equal(t, \"test.py\", listResp.Files[0].Name)\n1049:         \n1050:         // 5. Download file\n1051:         resp = doRequest(t, \"GET\", \"http://localhost:\"+strconv.Itoa(testPort)+\"/api/files/test.py\", nil, token)\n1052:         require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n1053:         \n1054:         content, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n1055:         require.Equal(t, \"print('hello')\", string(content))\n1056:     })\n1057: }\n1058: \n1059: func doRequest(t *testing.T, method, url string, body []byte, token string) *http.Response {\n1060:     var bodyReader io.Reader\n1061:     if body != nil {\n1062:         bodyReader = bytes.NewBuffer(body)\n1063:     }\n1064:     \n1065:     req, err := http.NewRequest(method, url, bodyReader)\n1066:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1067:     \n1068:     if token != \"\" {\n1069:         req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n1070:     }\n1071:     \n1072:     if body != nil {\n1073:         req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n1074:     }\n1075:     \n1076:     client := &http.Client{Timeout: 10 * time.Second}\n1077:     resp, err := client.Do(req)\n1078:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1079:     \n1080:     return resp\n1081: }\n1082: ```\n1083: \n1084: ## Dependencies\n1085: \n1086: ### Go Module Dependencies\n1087: \n1088: ```go\n1089: require (\n1090:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n1091:     github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0\n1092:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n1093:     github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0\n1094: )\n1095: ```\n1096: \n1097: ### External Dependencies\n1098: \n1099: - **Gin Framework**: HTTP routing and middleware\n1100: - **JWT Library**: RSA-based JWT token validation\n1101: - **klog**: Structured logging\n1102: - **Go Standard Library**: exec, os, filepath, time, context, crypto/rsa\n1103: \n1104: ## Security Considerations\n1105: \n1106: ### Authentication\n1107: \n1108: - All API endpoints (except `/health`) require JWT authentication\n1109: - JWT tokens must be signed with RSA private key\n1110: - PicoD validates tokens using the RSA public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n1111: - Invalid or expired tokens are rejected with HTTP 401\n1112: - Token validation includes expiration check, issued-at check, and 1-minute leeway\n1113: \n1114: ### Authorization\n1115: \n1116: - Path sanitization ensures all file operations stay within workspace jail\n1117: - Symlink resolution and validation prevents escape via symbolic links\n1118: - No special authorization beyond JWT authentication - all authenticated users have full access to workspace\n1119: \n1120: ### Input Validation\n1121: \n1122: - Command execution validates non-empty command array\n1123: - Timeout values are validated using Go's `time.ParseDuration`\n1124: - File paths are sanitized to prevent directory traversal\n1125: - Request body size limited to 32 MiB after JWT validation\n1126: - File modes are validated and clamped to maximum of 0777\n1127: \n1128: ### Error Messages\n1129: \n1130: - Error messages do not expose sensitive information\n1131: - File paths in error messages are relative to workspace\n1132: - Detailed authentication errors are logged but not exposed to clients\n1133: \n1134: ### Logging\n1135: \n1136: - klog used for structured logging\n1137: - Sensitive data (JWT tokens, file contents) are not logged\n1138: - Errors are logged with appropriate severity levels\n1139: \n1140: ## Integration Points\n1141: \n1142: ### With AgentCube Platform\n1143: \n1144: PicoD integrates with AgentCube components:\n1145: \n1146: - **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Includes PicoD container in sandbox pods\n1147: - **Router**: Forwards code execution requests to PicoD instances\n1148: - **WorkloadManager**: Manages PicoD lifecycle and health checks\n1149: - **Session Store**: Stores metadata about PicoD sessions\n1150: \n1151: ### Deployment Integration\n1152: \n1153: ```\n1154: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n1155: │                    Sandbox Pod                                   │\n1156: │                                                                  │\n1157: │  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────┐ │\n1158: │  │   Code Interpreter   │  │           PicoD                  │ │\n1159: │  │   (User Container)   │  │   (Sidecar Container)            │ │\n1160: │  │                      │  │                                  │ │\n1161: │  │  - Python/Node.js    │  │  - HTTP Server (:8080)          │ │\n1162: │  │  - User Code         │  │  - JWT Auth                      │ │\n1163: │  │  - Dependencies      │  │  - Command Execution             │ │\n1164: │  │                      │  │  - File Management               │ │\n1165: │  └──────────────────────┘  │                                  │ │\n1166: │           │                └──────────────────────────────────┘ │\n1167: │           │                              │                       │\n1168: │           ▼                              ▼                       │\n1169: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n1170: │  │              Shared Volume (Workspace)                    │   │\n1171: │  │  - User files                                             │   │\n1172: │  │  - Code artifacts                                         │   │\n1173: │  │  - Execution outputs                                      │   │\n1174: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n1175: │                                                                  │\n1176: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n1177: ```\n1178: \n1179: ## Configuration\n1180: \n1181: ### CLI Flags\n1182: \n1183: | Flag      | Type   | Default | Description |\n1184: |-----------|--------|---------|-------------|\n1185: | `-port`   | int    | 8080    | Port for the PicoD server to listen on |\n1186: | `-workspace` | string | \"\"      | Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory) |\n1187: \n1188: ### Environment Variables\n1189: \n1190: | Name                      | Required | Description |\n1191: |---------------------------|----------|-------------|\n1192: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`   | Yes      | PEM-encoded RSA public key for JWT validation |\n1193: \n1194: ### Configuration File (Optional)\n1195: \n1196: PicoD can be configured via a ConfigMap or environment variables:\n1197: \n1198: ```yaml\n1199: # ConfigMap example\n1200: apiVersion: v1\n1201: kind: ConfigMap\n1202: metadata:\n1203:   name: picod-config\n1204: data:\n1205:   PORT: \"8080\"\n1206:   WORKSPACE: \"/workspace\"\n1207:   PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY: |\n1208:     -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n1209:     MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n1210:     -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n1211: ```\n1212: \n1213: ## Documentation\n1214: \n1215: ### API Documentation\n1216: \n1217: All API endpoints should be documented using OpenAPI/Swagger:\n1218: \n1219: ```yaml\n1220: openapi: 3.0.0\n1221: info:\n1222:   title: PicoD API\n1223:   version: 0.0.1\n1224:   description: Secure command execution and file management API\n1225: \n1226: paths:\n1227:   /api/execute:\n1228:     post:\n1229:       summary: Execute a command\n1230:       security:\n1231:         - BearerAuth: []\n1232:       requestBody:\n1233:         required: true\n1234:         content:\n1235:           application/json:\n1236:             schema:\n1237:               $ref: '#/components/schemas/ExecuteRequest'\n1238:       responses:\n1239:         '200':\n1240:           description: Command executed successfully\n1241:           content:\n1242:             application/json:\n1243:               schema:\n1244:                 $ref: '#/components/schemas/ExecuteResponse'\n1245: \n1246:   /health:\n1247:     get:\n1248:       summary: Health check\n1249:       responses:\n1250:         '200':\n1251:           description: Service is healthy\n1252:           content:\n1253:             application/json:\n1254:               schema:\n1255:                 type: object\n1256:                 properties:\n1257:                   status:\n1258:                     type: string\n1259:                   service:\n1260:                     type: string\n1261:                   version:\n1262:                     type: string\n1263:                   uptime:\n1264:                     type: string\n1265: \n1266: components:\n1267:   securitySchemes:\n1268:     BearerAuth:\n1269:       type: http\n1270:       scheme: bearer\n1271:       bearerFormat: JWT\n1272: ```\n1273: \n1274: ### Usage Examples\n1275: \n1276: **Starting PicoD**:\n1277: ```bash\n1278: # With default settings\n1279: ./picod\n1280: \n1281: # With custom port and workspace\n1282: ./picod -port 9090 -workspace /data/workspace\n1283: \n1284: # With klog flags\n1285: ./picod -port 8080 -v=2\n1286: ```\n1287: \n1288: **Making API requests**:\n1289: ```bash\n1290: # Health check (no auth)\n1291: curl http://localhost:8080/health\n1292: \n1293: # Execute command (with JWT)\n1294: export TOKEN=\"<your-jwt-token>\"\n1295: curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/execute \\\n1296:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n1297:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n1298:   -d '{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"hello world\"]}'\n1299: \n1300: # Upload file (JSON Base64)\n1301: curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/files \\\n1302:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n1303:   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n1304:   -d '{\"path\":\"test.txt\",\"content\":\"SGVsbG8gd29ybGQ=\"}'\n1305: \n1306: # Upload file (multipart)\n1307: curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/files \\\n1308:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n1309:   -F \"path=test.txt\" \\\n1310:   -F \"file=@local.txt\"\n1311: \n1312: # List files\n1313: curl \"http://localhost:8080/api/files?path=.\" \\\n1314:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n1315: \n1316: # Download file\n1317: curl \"http://localhost:8080/api/files/test.txt\" \\\n1318:   -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n1319:   -O -J\n1320: ```\n1321: \n1322: ## Success Criteria\n1323: \n1324: - [ ] HTTP server initializes with configurable port and workspace\n1325: - [ ] JWT authentication middleware correctly validates tokens\n1326: - [ ] Command execution API handles timeout and captures output\n1327: - [ ] File upload API supports both multipart and JSON Base64 formats\n1328: - [ ] File listing API returns directory contents\n1329: - [ ] File download API serves files with proper headers\n1330: - [ ] Health check endpoint responds without authentication\n1331: - [ ] Path sanitization prevents workspace escape\n1332: - [ ] Error responses follow consistent format\n1333: - [ ] Graceful shutdown handles existing connections\n1334: - [ ] Unit tests cover all major code paths\n1335: - [ ] Integration tests validate end-to-end workflows\n1336: - [ ] Security measures (JWT, path sanitization) are effective\n1337: - [ ] Logging provides visibility without exposing sensitive data\n1338: - [ ] CLI flags and environment variables work correctly\n\n(End of file - total 1338 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PicoD 命令执行 API Design\n\n## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Implement a secure HTTP daemon for command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail, providing JWT-protected APIs for code interpreter sandboxes in the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs. It serves as the core execution engine for code interpreter sandboxes, enabling secure code execution, file operations (upload, list, download), and health monitoring with proper authentication.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- HTTP server with configurable port and workspace directory\n- JWT (RSA) authentication for all API endpoints except health check\n- Command execution API with timeout support\n- File management APIs (upload, list, download)\n- Path security to enforce workspace jail\n- Support for multipart and JSON Base64 file uploads","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775860779164,"end":1775860779188}}}}
