{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860884950,"sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","part":{"id":"prt_d798ea4900018dyoLKLslgI0Dh","messageID":"msg_d798d3aa8001lBXek2Ej552Lhu","sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-020a197d19f6488398662cc92a9c976a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n\n## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Implement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for PicoD, providing secure session authentication for the AgentCube platform by validating incoming request tokens and protecting sensitive API endpoints.\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD JWT middleware provides a comprehensive authentication layer that validates JWT tokens using RSA public key verification. The middleware intercepts all requests to protected API endpoints, extracts and validates Bearer tokens from the Authorization header, and ensures only properly authenticated requests can access file operations and code execution APIs. The implementation follows RFC 6750 Bearer Token usage standards and RS256 signature verification with clock skew tolerance.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- JWT token validation using RSA public key (RS256 algorithm)\n- Public key loaded from environment variable (`PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`)\n- Bearer token format extraction and validation\n- Token expiration checking with 1-minute leeway\n- Protection of `/api/*` routes with authentication middleware\n- Public access to `/health` endpoint for Kubernetes probes\n- Structured error responses for all authentication failures\n- Request body size limiting (32MB) after authentication\n- Concurrent-safe public key access with read-write mutex\n- Comprehensive error handling and logging\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── auth.go                # AuthManager, AuthClaims, token validation\n├── middleware.go          # AuthMiddleware, request interception\n├── errors.go              # Error types, status code mapping (extended)\n├── constants.go           # Environment variables, error messages (extended)\n├── server.go              # Server integration, auth manager initialization (modified)\n├── auth_test.go           # Unit tests for authentication\n└── server_test.go         # Integration tests (extended)\n\nchanges/AR-017/\n├── design.md              # This document\n├── spec.md                # API specification\n├── proposal.md            # Design proposal\n├── delta-spec.md          # Detailed requirements\n├── CHANGE.md              # Change log\n└── README.md              # Implementation notes\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        PicoD HTTP Server                            │\n│                                                                      │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │              Gin HTTP Engine                                   │ │\n│  │  - Global middleware: Logger, Recovery                         │ │\n│  │  - /api routes with JWT auth                                  │ │\n│  │  - /health route (no auth)                                    │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                              │                                       │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │              AuthMiddleware (Gin middleware)                   │ │\n│  │  1. Extract Authorization header                               │ │\n│  │  2. Validate Bearer format                                     │ │\n│  │  3. Call AuthManager.ValidateToken()                          │ │\n│  │  4. Store claims in context                                    │ │\n│  │  5. Apply body size limit (32MB)                               │ │\n│  │  6. Call c.Next() or Abort()                                   │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                              │                                       │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │              AuthManager                                      │ │\n│  │  - publicKey: *rsa.PublicKey (cached, mutex-protected)        │ │\n│  │  - mutex: sync.RWMutex (concurrent-safe)                     │ │\n│  │                                                                │ │\n│  │  ValidateToken():                                             │ │\n│  │  1. Acquire read lock                                         │ │\n│  │  2. Parse JWT with Claims                                     │ │\n│  │  3. Verify signing method is RSA                             │ │\n│  │  4. Verify signature with public key                         │ │\n│  │  5. Validate expiration (with 1min leeway)                    │ │\n│  │  6. Release read lock                                         │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                              │                                       │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │              Error Handling                                   │ │\n│  │  - NewError() creates PicoDError                             │ │\n│  │  - HandleError() maps to HTTP status codes                    │ │\n│  │  - Structured JSON error responses                           │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Environment Variables                            │\n│                                                                     │\n│  PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY                                             │\n│  -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----                                         │\n│  MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...                   │\n│  -----END PUBLIC KEY---                                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nHTTP Request to /api/execute\n    ↓\n[Gin Global Middleware] Logger, Recovery\n    ↓\n[Route Matching] Matches /api/* route group\n    ↓\n[AuthMiddleware]\n    ↓\n1. Extract Authorization header\n    ↓\n2. Check header exists?\n    ├─ No → Return 401: \"Missing Authorization header\"\n    └─ Yes ↓\n3. Check starts with \"Bearer \"?\n    ├─ No → Return 401: \"Use Bearer <token> format\"\n    └─ Yes ↓\n4. Extract token (trim \"Bearer \" prefix)\n    ↓\n5. Call AuthManager.ValidateToken(token)\n    ├─ Error → Log warning, Return 401: \"Invalid token\"\n    └─ Success ↓\n6. Store claims in Gin context (c.Set(\"claims\", claims))\n    ↓\n7. Apply body size limit (http.MaxBytesReader, 32MB)\n    ↓\n8. Call c.Next()\n    ↓\n[Handler Processing] ExecuteHandler, UploadFileHandler, etc.\n    ↓\nHTTP Response\n```\n\n### Authentication Initialization Flow\n\n```\nServer startup (NewServer)\n    ↓\n1. Create workspace directory\n    ↓\n2. Call NewAuthManager()\n    ↓\n3. Read PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var\n    ├─ Not set → Return error (server fails to start)\n    └─ Set ↓\n4. Decode PEM block\n    ├─ Invalid → Return error (server fails to start)\n    └─ Valid ↓\n5. Parse PKIX public key\n    ├─ Error → Return error (server fails to start)\n    └─ Success ↓\n6. Validate it's an RSA key\n    ├─ Not RSA → Return error (server fails to start)\n    └─ Valid ↓\n7. Create AuthManager with publicKey\n    ↓\n8. Log \"Auth manager initialized successfully\"\n    ↓\n9. Create Gin engine\n    ↓\n10. Register routes\n    ├─ /api routes → Apply AuthMiddleware\n    └─ /health route → No middleware\n    ↓\n11. Return Server instance\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Auth Manager\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n\n```go\n// AuthManager manages JWT authentication with RSA public key\ntype AuthManager struct {\n\tpublicKey *rsa.PublicKey  // RSA public key for token verification\n\tmutex     sync.RWMutex    // Protects publicKey from concurrent access\n}\n\n// NewAuthManager creates a new AuthManager by loading public key from environment\nfunc NewAuthManager() (*AuthManager, error)\n\n// ValidateToken validates a JWT token and returns claims\nfunc (am *AuthManager) ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*AuthClaims, error)\n```\n\n### Auth Claims\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n\n```go\n// AuthClaims represents JWT claims with standard registered claims\ntype AuthClaims struct {\n\tjwt.RegisteredClaims  // Includes: Issuer, Subject, ExpiresAt, IssuedAt, NotBefore, ID\n}\n```\n\n### Authentication Error Types\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go` (Extended)\n\n```go\nconst (\n\t// Authentication error codes\n\tErrMissingAuthHeader = \"MissingAuthHeader\"   // Authorization header missing\n\tErrInvalidAuthFormat = \"InvalidAuthFormat\"   // Not \"Bearer <token>\" format\n\tErrInvalidToken      = \"InvalidToken\"        // Token validation failed\n\tErrInvalidSignature  = \"InvalidSignature\"    // Invalid signing method\n\tErrTokenExpired      = \"TokenExpired\"        // Token expired\n\tErrInvalidPublicKey  = \"InvalidPublicKey\"    // Public key loading failed\n)\n\nvar statusCodeMap = map[string]int{\n\tErrMissingAuthHeader: http.StatusUnauthorized,      // 401\n\tErrInvalidAuthFormat: http.StatusUnauthorized,      // 401\n\tErrInvalidToken:      http.StatusUnauthorized,      // 401\n\tErrInvalidSignature:  http.StatusUnauthorized,      // 401\n\tErrTokenExpired:      http.StatusUnauthorized,      // 401\n\tErrInvalidPublicKey:  http.StatusInternalServerError, // 500\n}\n```\n\n### Error Response\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n\n```go\n// ErrorResponse represents a standardized error response\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n\tError  string `json:\"error\"`\n\tCode   int    `json:\"code\"`\n\tDetail string `json:\"detail,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Server Integration\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/server.go` (Modified)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n\tengine      *gin.Engine\n\tconfig      Config\n\tauthManager *AuthManager  // Added: JWT authentication manager\n\tstartTime   time.Time\n\tworkspaceDir string\n\thttpServer  *http.Server\n\t// ... other fields\n}\n\nfunc NewServer(config Config) (*Server, error) {\n\t// ... workspace setup ...\n\n\t// Initialize AuthManager (fails if public key not configured)\n\tauthManager, err := NewAuthManager()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\tserver := &Server{\n\t\tengine:      engine,\n\t\tconfig:      config,\n\t\tauthManager: authManager,\n\t\t// ... other fields\n\t}\n\n\tserver.registerRoutes()\n\treturn server, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n\t// Protect all /api/* routes with authentication\n\tapi := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n\tapi.Use(AuthMiddleware(s.authManager))\n\t{\n\t\tapi.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n\t\tapi.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n\t\tapi.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n\t\tapi.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n\t}\n\n\t// Health check remains public for Kubernetes probes\n\ts.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/constants.go` (Extended)\n\n```go\nconst (\n\t// Environment variables\n\tPublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"  // RSA public key PEM\n\n\t// HTTP headers\n\tHeaderAuthorization = \"Authorization\"\n\n\t// Error messages\n\tErrMsgMissingAuthHeader = \"Missing Authorization header\"\n\tErrMsgInvalidAuthFormat = \"Use Bearer <token> format\"\n\tErrMsgInvalidToken      = \"Invalid token\"\n\n\t// Size limits\n\tMaxBodySize = 32 << 20  // 32MB request body limit\n)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Authentication Flow\n\n**Authorization Header Format**:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt_token>\n```\n\n**JWT Token Structure** (RS256):\n```json\n{\n  \"header\": {\n    \"alg\": \"RS256\",\n    \"typ\": \"JWT\"\n  },\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n    \"sub\": \"session-id\",\n    \"exp\": 1704067200,\n    \"iat\": 1704063600,\n    \"nbf\": 1704063600,\n    \"jti\": \"token-id\"\n  },\n  \"signature\": \"<rsa-signature>\"\n}\n```\n\n### Protected Endpoints\n\nAll `/api/*` endpoints require valid JWT authentication:\n\n- **POST /api/execute** - Command execution\n- **POST /api/files** - File upload\n- **GET /api/files** - File listing\n- **GET /api/files/*path** - File download\n\n### Public Endpoint\n\n- **GET /health** - Health check (no authentication required)\n\n### Error Responses\n\n**Missing Authorization Header** (HTTP 401):\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Missing Authorization header\",\n  \"code\": 401,\n  \"detail\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n**Invalid Authorization Format** (HTTP 401):\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Use Bearer <token> format\",\n  \"code\": 401,\n  \"detail\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n**Invalid Token** (HTTP 401):\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid token\",\n  \"code\": 401,\n  \"detail\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n**Token Expired** (HTTP 401):\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid token\",\n  \"code\": 401,\n  \"detail\": \"\"\n}\n```\n\n**Invalid Public Key** (HTTP 500):\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"public key not found\",\n  \"code\": 500,\n  \"detail\": \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY environment variable is not set\"\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Authentication Errors\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n\n```go\nfunc NewAuthManager() (*AuthManager, error) {\n\tpublicKeyPEM := os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n\tif publicKeyPEM == \"\" {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrInvalidPublicKey, \"public key not found\",\n\t\t\t\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY environment variable is not set\", nil)\n\t}\n\n\tblock, _ := pem.Decode([]byte(publicKeyPEM))\n\tif block == nil {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrInvalidPublicKey, \"invalid PEM format\",\n\t\t\t\"failed to decode PEM block\", nil)\n\t}\n\n\tpubKey, err := x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrInvalidPublicKey, \"failed to parse public key\",\n\t\t\terr.Error(), err)\n\t}\n\n\trsaPublicKey, ok := pubKey.(*rsa.PublicKey)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrInvalidPublicKey, \"not an RSA public key\",\n\t\t\t\"expected RSA public key\", nil)\n\t}\n\n\tklog.Info(\"Auth manager initialized successfully\")\n\treturn &AuthManager{publicKey: rsaPublicKey}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (am *AuthManager) ValidateToken(tokenString string) (*AuthClaims, error) {\n\tam.mutex.RLock()\n\tdefer am.mutex.RUnlock()\n\n\ttoken, err := jwt.ParseWithClaims(tokenString, &AuthClaims{},\n\t\tfunc(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n\t\t\tif _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected signing method: %v\", token.Header[\"alg\"])\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn am.publicKey, nil\n\t\t},\n\t\tjwt.WithLeeway(1*time.Minute))\n\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrInvalidToken, \"invalid token\", \"\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif claims, ok := token.Claims.(*AuthClaims); ok && token.Valid {\n\t\treturn claims, nil\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil, NewError(ErrInvalidToken, \"invalid token claims\", \"\", nil)\n}\n```\n\n### Middleware Error Handling\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/middleware.go`\n\n```go\nfunc AuthMiddleware(authManager *AuthManager) gin.HandlerFunc {\n\treturn func(c *gin.Context) {\n\t\tauthHeader := c.GetHeader(HeaderAuthorization)\n\t\tif authHeader == \"\" {\n\t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrMissingAuthHeader, ErrMsgMissingAuthHeader, \"\", nil))\n\t\t\tc.Abort()\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif !strings.HasPrefix(authHeader, \"Bearer \") {\n\t\t\tHandleError(c, NewError(ErrInvalidAuthFormat, ErrMsgInvalidAuthFormat, \"\", nil))\n\t\t\tc.Abort()\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\n\t\ttoken := strings.TrimPrefix(authHeader, \"Bearer \")\n\t\tclaims, err := authManager.ValidateToken(token)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Token validation failed: %v\", err)\n\t\t\tHandleError(c, err)\n\t\t\tc.Abort()\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tc.Set(\"claims\", claims)\n\t\tc.Request.Body = http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)\n\t\tc.Next()\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Error Recovery Strategy\n\n1. **Startup Errors**:\n   - Public key not found: Server fails to start\n   - Invalid PEM format: Server fails to start\n   - Non-RSA key: Server fails to start\n   - Purpose: Fail-fast prevents running with broken authentication\n\n2. **Runtime Errors**:\n   - Missing header: Return 401, log warning\n   - Invalid format: Return 401, log warning\n   - Invalid token: Return 401, log warning\n   - Expired token: Return 401, log warning\n   - Purpose: Graceful rejection without exposing sensitive details\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/auth_test.go`\n\n```go\n// Test AuthManager initialization\nfunc TestNewAuthManager(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname     string\n\t\tsetupEnv func()\n\t\twantErr  bool\n\t\terrMsg   string\n\t\tcleanup  func()\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"success with valid public key\",\n\t\t\tsetupEnv: func() {\n\t\t\t\tos.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, validPublicKeyPEM)\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"error when public key not set\",\n\t\t\tsetupEnv: func() {\n\t\t\t\tos.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: true,\n\t\t\terrMsg:  \"public key not found\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"error with invalid PEM format\",\n\t\t\tsetupEnv: func() {\n\t\t\t\tos.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, \"invalid pem\")\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: true,\n\t\t\terrMsg:  \"invalid PEM format\",\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\ttt.setupEnv()\n\t\t\tdefer tt.cleanup()\n\n\t\t\tam, err := NewAuthManager()\n\t\t\tif tt.wantErr {\n\t\t\t\tassert.Error(t, err)\n\t\t\t\tassert.Nil(t, am)\n\t\t\t\tif tt.errMsg != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), tt.errMsg)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\t\t\t\tassert.NotNil(t, am)\n\t\t\t\tassert.NotNil(t, am.publicKey)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\n// Test token validation\nfunc TestValidateToken(t *testing.T) {\n\tprivateKey, publicKey := generateTestKeyPair(t)\n\tpublicKeyPEM := publicKeyToPEM(t, publicKey)\n\n\tos.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, publicKeyPEM)\n\tdefer os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n\n\tam, err := NewAuthManager()\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tvalidToken := createTestToken(t, privateKey)\n\texpiredToken := createExpiredToken(t, privateKey)\n\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname        string\n\t\ttoken       string\n\t\twantErr     bool\n\t\terrContains string\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:    \"valid token\",\n\t\t\ttoken:   validToken,\n\t\t\twantErr: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:        \"invalid token format\",\n\t\t\ttoken:       \"invalid.token.string\",\n\t\t\twantErr:     true,\n\t\t\terrContains: \"invalid token\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:        \"expired token\",\n\t\t\ttoken:       expiredToken,\n\t\t\twantErr:     true,\n\t\t\terrContains: \"expired\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:        \"empty token\",\n\t\t\ttoken:       \"\",\n\t\t\twantErr:     true,\n\t\t\terrContains: \"invalid token\",\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tclaims, err := am.ValidateToken(tt.token)\n\t\t\tif tt.wantErr {\n\t\t\t\tassert.Error(t, err)\n\t\t\t\tassert.Nil(t, claims)\n\t\t\t\tif tt.errContains != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tassert.Contains(t, err.Error(), tt.errContains)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\t\t\t\tassert.NotNil(t, claims)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/server_test.go` (Extended)\n\n```go\nfunc TestAuthenticationIntegration(t *testing.T) {\n\tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n\n\tprivateKey, publicKey := generateTestKeyPair(t)\n\tpublicKeyPEM := publicKeyToPEM(t, publicKey)\n\n\tos.Setenv(PublicKeyEnvVar, publicKeyPEM)\n\tdefer os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)\n\n\tconfig := Config{\n\t\tPort:      testPort,\n\t\tWorkspace: workspace,\n\t}\n\n\tserver, err := NewServer(config)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tgo func() {\n\t\tif err := server.Run(); err != nil && !errors.Is(err, http.ErrServerClosed) {\n\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n\t\t}\n\t}()\n\n\ttime.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)\n\n\tdefer func() {\n\t\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n\t\tdefer cancel()\n\t\tserver.Shutdown(ctx)\n\t}()\n\n\tt.Run(\"public health check\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tresp := doRequest(t, \"GET\", \"http://localhost:8080/health\", nil, \"\")\n\t\trequire.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"protected endpoint requires auth\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tresp := doRequest(t, \"POST\", \"http://localhost:8080/api/execute\",\n\t\t\t[]byte(`{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"test\"]}`), \"\")\n\t\trequire.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, resp.StatusCode)\n\n\t\tvar errResp ErrorResponse\n\t\tjson.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&errResp)\n\t\tassert.Equal(t, ErrMsgMissingAuthHeader, errResp.Error)\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"valid token grants access\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\ttoken := createTestToken(t, privateKey)\n\t\tresp := doRequest(t, \"POST\", \"http://localhost:8080/api/execute\",\n\t\t\t[]byte(`{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"test\"]}`), token)\n\t\trequire.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"invalid token rejected\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tresp := doRequest(t, \"POST\", \"http://localhost:8080/api/execute\",\n\t\t\t[]byte(`{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"test\"]}`), \"invalid.token\")\n\t\trequire.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, resp.StatusCode)\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Public Key Security\n\n- **Environment Variable Injection**: Public key is injected via `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable, typically from Kubernetes Secret\n- **PEM Validation**: Strict PEM format validation prevents injection attacks\n- **Type Verification**: Ensures key is RSA type before accepting\n- **No Logging**: Public key content is never logged to prevent exposure\n\n### Token Validation\n\n- **Signature Algorithm**: Only accepts RS256 (RSA with SHA-256), rejects other algorithms\n- **Signature Verification**: Uses cached RSA public key to verify JWT signatures\n- **Expiration Check**: Strict expiration validation with 1-minute leeway for clock skew\n- **Registered Claims**: Validates standard JWT claims (iss, sub, exp, iat, nbf, jti)\n- **Algorithm Confusion**: Prevents algorithm confusion attacks by explicitly checking signing method\n\n### Request Security\n\n- **Header Extraction**: Only extracts from `Authorization` header, not from URL or body\n- **Bearer Format**: Enforces RFC 6750 Bearer token format\n- **Body Size Limit**: 32MB limit prevents large payload attacks after authentication\n- **Context Isolation**: Claims stored in Gin context, not exposed in responses\n\n### Error Handling Security\n\n- **Generic Errors**: Returns generic error messages to clients (no sensitive details)\n- **Logging**: Detailed errors logged server-side for auditing\n- **Status Codes**: Maps to appropriate HTTP status codes (401 for auth failures)\n- **No Leakage**: Does not expose public key content, token internals, or system details\n\n### Concurrent Safety\n\n- **Read-Write Mutex**: Protects public key from concurrent access during validation\n- **Read Lock**: Acquires read lock during token validation (allows concurrent reads)\n- **No Write Operations**: Public key is write-once at initialization, no runtime updates\n- **Goroutine Safe**: Middleware can handle concurrent requests safely\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With AgentCube Router\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Router Module                            │\n│                                                              │\n│  - Generates JWT tokens (RSA private key)                   │\n│  - Issues tokens to authenticated sessions                  │\n│  - Tokens include session ID, expiration, user info          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            │ JWT Token\n                            │\n┌───────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      PicoD Instance                          │\n│                                                              │\n│  - Receives requests with Authorization: Bearer <token>      │\n│  - Validates token using RSA public key                     │\n│  - Allows access to /api/* endpoints if valid               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Distribution\n\n- **Router**: Holds RSA private key for token generation\n- **PicoD**: Receives RSA public key via environment variable\n- **Distribution**: Kubernetes Secret, ConfigMap, or environment variable\n- **Rotation**: Requires PicoD restart for key updates\n\n### Kubernetes Deployment\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-auth-keys\ntype: Opaque\nstringData:\n  public-key: |\n    -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n    MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n    -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-pod\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: picod\n    image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n    env:\n    - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n      valueFrom:\n        secretKeyRef:\n          name: picod-auth-keys\n          key: public-key\n```\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\nPicoD service account does not require special RBAC for authentication:\n- Authentication is handled by HTTP layer, not Kubernetes API\n- No service account token usage for JWT validation\n- Public key is static configuration, not retrieved from cluster\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable Name | Required | Description | Example |\n|--------------|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Yes | PEM-encoded RSA public key for JWT validation | `-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\\nMIIBIjANBgkqh...\\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----` |\n\n### HTTP Headers\n\n| Header Name | Format | Example |\n|-------------|--------|---------|\n| `Authorization` | `Bearer <jwt_token>` | `Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...` |\n\n### CLI Flags (Unchanged)\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n| `-workspace` | string | \"\" | Workspace directory |\n\n### Configuration Example\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-config\ndata:\n  PORT: \"8080\"\n  WORKSPACE: \"/workspace\"\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-auth-secret\ntype: Opaque\nstringData:\n  public-key: |\n    -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n    MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEAxWu...\n    -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: picod\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: picod\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: picod\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: picod\n        image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n        env:\n        - name: PORT\n          valueFrom:\n            configMapKeyRef:\n              name: picod-config\n              key: PORT\n        - name: WORKSPACE\n          valueFrom:\n            configMapKeyRef:\n              name: picod-config\n              key: WORKSPACE\n        - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: picod-auth-secret\n              key: public-key\n        volumeMounts:\n        - name: workspace\n          mountPath: /workspace\n      volumes:\n      - name: workspace\n        emptyDir: {}\n```\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Token Validation Performance\n\n- **RSA Verification**: ~1-5ms per token (2048-bit key)\n- **Public Key Caching**: Key loaded once at startup, in-memory cache\n- **Concurrent Validation**: Read lock allows concurrent token validations\n- **No External Calls**: No network calls or database queries during validation\n\n### Resource Usage\n\n- **Memory**: ~256 bytes for 2048-bit RSA public key\n- **CPU**: RSA verification during each request\n- **Network**: No additional network overhead\n- **Storage**: None (public key in memory only)\n\n### Scalability\n\n- **Horizontal Scaling**: Each PicoD instance has its own auth manager\n- **No Shared State**: Auth manager is per-instance, no inter-instance coordination\n- **Load Balancing**: JWT validation happens before handler logic, no state dependency\n\n## Monitoring and Metrics\n\n### Key Metrics (Recommended)\n\n- `auth_validation_total`: Total token validation attempts\n- `auth_validation_success_total`: Successful token validations\n- `auth_validation_failure_total`: Failed token validations\n- `auth_validation_duration_seconds`: Token validation latency\n- `auth_error_missing_header_total`: Missing Authorization header errors\n- `auth_error_invalid_format_total`: Invalid Bearer format errors\n- `auth_error_invalid_token_total`: Invalid token errors\n- `auth_error_expired_token_total`: Expired token errors\n\n### Logging\n\n- **Info Level**: \"Auth manager initialized successfully\" on startup\n- **Warning Level**: \"Token validation failed: <error>\" on auth failures\n- **Error Level**: Not used for authentication (failures are warnings)\n\n### Health Check\n\n- **Status**: Auth manager status included in health check (future enhancement)\n- **Dependency**: Server startup fails if auth manager cannot initialize\n- **Probe**: `/health` endpoint works even if auth fails (no auth required)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Go Module Dependencies\n\n```go\nrequire (\n    github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n    github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0\n    k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n    github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0\n)\n```\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n- **Gin Framework**: HTTP routing and middleware (existing)\n- **golang-jwt/jwt**: JWT token parsing and validation (new)\n- **klog**: Structured logging (existing)\n- **Go Standard Library**:\n  - `crypto/rsa`: RSA public key operations\n  - `crypto/x509`: PKIX public key parsing\n  - `encoding/pem`: PEM encoding/decoding\n  - `sync`: Concurrent access protection\n  - `time`: Time utilities for token expiration\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] AuthManager successfully initializes with valid public key from environment\n- [ ] AuthManager fails to initialize when public key is missing or invalid\n- [ ] AuthMiddleware correctly extracts Bearer token from Authorization header\n- [ ] AuthMiddleware rejects requests without Authorization header (401)\n- [ ] AuthMiddleware rejects requests with invalid Bearer format (401)\n- [ ] AuthManager validates JWT tokens signed with corresponding private key\n- [ ] AuthManager rejects tokens with invalid signatures (401)\n- [ ] AuthManager rejects expired tokens (401)\n- [ ] AuthManager accepts valid tokens within 1-minute clock skew tolerance\n- [ ] AuthMiddleware stores validated claims in Gin context\n- [ ] AuthMiddleware applies 32MB body size limit after authentication\n- [ ] `/api/*` routes are protected by authentication middleware\n- [ ] `/health` endpoint remains publicly accessible\n- [ ] Error responses follow consistent JSON format\n- [ ] Public key access is thread-safe with read-write mutex\n- [ ] Unit tests cover AuthManager initialization and token validation\n- [ ] Unit tests cover middleware error scenarios\n- [ ] Integration tests validate end-to-end authentication flow\n- [ ] Logging provides visibility without exposing sensitive data\n- [ ] Security measures (RS256, algorithm checking, expiration) are effective\n- [ ] Performance overhead of token validation is acceptable\n\n## Documentation\n\n### API Documentation\n\n**Authentication Required Endpoints**:\n\n```yaml\npaths:\n  /api/execute:\n    post:\n      summary: Execute a command\n      security:\n        - BearerAuth: []\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n        content:\n          application/json:\n            schema:\n              type: object\n              properties:\n                command:\n                  type: array\n                  items:\n                    type: string\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Command executed successfully\n        '401':\n          description: Authentication required\n\n  /api/files:\n    post:\n      summary: Upload a file\n      security:\n        - BearerAuth: []\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: File uploaded successfully\n        '401':\n          description: Authentication required\n\n  /health:\n    get:\n      summary: Health check\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Service is healthy\n\ncomponents:\n  securitySchemes:\n    BearerAuth:\n      type: http\n      scheme: bearer\n      bearerFormat: JWT\n      description: JWT token issued by Router\n```\n\n### Usage Examples\n\n**Starting PicoD with Authentication**:\n```bash\n# Set public key environment variable\nexport PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY=\"-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\nMIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----\"\n\n# Start PicoD\n./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace\n```\n\n**Making Authenticated Requests**:\n```bash\n# Get JWT token from Router\nexport TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST https://router/token \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"session_id\":\"my-session\"}' | jq -r '.token')\n\n# Execute command (with JWT)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/execute \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"hello\"]}'\n\n# Upload file (with JWT)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/files \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -F \"path=test.txt\" \\\n  -F \"file=@local.txt\"\n\n# List files (with JWT)\ncurl \"http://localhost:8080/api/files?path=.\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n\n# Download file (with JWT)\ncurl \"http://localhost:8080/api/files/test.txt\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -O -J\n\n# Health check (no auth)\ncurl http://localhost:8080/health\n```\n\n### Testing Examples\n\n**Testing Authentication**:\n```go\n// Create test key pair\nprivateKey, publicKey := generateTestKeyPair()\npublicKeyPEM := publicKeyToPEM(publicKey)\n\n// Initialize AuthManager with test key\nos.Setenv(\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\", publicKeyPEM)\nauthManager, _ := NewAuthManager()\n\n// Create valid token\nclaims := AuthClaims{\n    RegisteredClaims: jwt.RegisteredClaims{\n        ExpiresAt: jwt.NewNumericDate(time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour)),\n    },\n}\ntoken := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, claims)\ntokenString, _ := token.SignedString(privateKey)\n\n// Validate token\nvalidatedClaims, err := authManager.ValidateToken(tokenString)\nassert.NoError(t, err)\nassert.NotNil(t, validatedClaims)\n```\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- **No Breaking Changes**: Existing API endpoints unchanged, only added authentication requirement\n- **Opt-in**: Authentication is enabled by default via environment variable\n- **Graceful Failure**: Server fails to start if public key not configured (fail-fast)\n\n### Upgrading from Previous Versions\n\nTo enable JWT authentication on existing PicoD deployments:\n\n1. **Generate RSA Key Pair** (on Router):\n   ```bash\n   openssl genrsa -out private.pem 2048\n   openssl rsa -in private.pem -pubout -out public.pem\n   ```\n\n2. **Deploy Public Key** to PicoD:\n   ```bash\n   kubectl create secret generic picod-auth-keys \\\n     --from-file=public-key=public.pem\n   ```\n\n3. **Update PicoD Deployment** to inject public key:\n   ```yaml\n   env:\n   - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n     valueFrom:\n       secretKeyRef:\n         name: picod-auth-keys\n         key: public-key\n   ```\n\n4. **Update Client Code** to include JWT token:\n   ```bash\n   # Before\n   curl http://picod:8080/api/execute -d '{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"test\"]}'\n\n   # After\n   TOKEN=$(get-token-from-router)\n   curl http://picod:8080/api/execute \\\n     -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n     -d '{\"command\":[\"echo\",\"test\"]}'\n   ```\n\n### Key Rotation\n\nTo rotate RSA keys:\n\n1. **Generate new key pair** on Router\n2. **Update Router** to use new private key for token generation\n3. **Deploy new public key** to PicoD (update Secret)\n4. **Restart PicoD pods** to load new public key\n\n**Note**: There is currently no support for multiple keys or graceful key rotation. All PicoD instances must be restarted to pick up the new key. Tokens signed with the old key will be rejected after rotation.\n\n### Rollback Plan\n\nIf authentication causes issues:\n\n1. **Remove Public Key Environment Variable**: Server will fail to start\n2. **Disable Authentication**: Temporarily set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` to empty and comment out initialization (code change required)\n3. **Restore Previous Version**: Roll back to pre-authentication PicoD image\n\n**Warning**: Disabling authentication requires code changes and is not recommended for production use.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go\">\nERROR [117:47] cannot use mockStore (variable of type *mockStoreForGC) as store.Store value in argument to NewGarbageCollector: *mockStoreForGC does not implement store.Store (missing method GetSandboxBySessionID)\nERROR [145:47] cannot use mockStore (vari