{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860888135,"sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","part":{"id":"prt_d798eb222001bzVMGerQP2G2L9","messageID":"msg_d798ea6040015LwBkyY0STB6S6","sessionID":"ses_286737a50ffeDjXBfrGRT5Qp7n","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4a0a2e6bd1a9426f90f8d510d6d0f4f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Purpose**: Implement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for PicoD, providing secure session authentication for the AgentCube platform by validating incoming request tokens and protecting sensitive API endpoints.\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: PicoD JWT middleware provides a comprehensive authentication layer that validates JWT tokens using RSA public key verification. The middleware intercepts all requests to protected API endpoints, extracts and validates Bearer tokens from the Authorization header, and ensures only properly authenticated requests can access file operations and code execution APIs. The implementation follows RFC 6750 Bearer Token usage standards and RS256 signature verification with clock skew tolerance.\n12: \n13: ### Key Requirements\n14: \n15: - JWT token validation using RSA public key (RS256 algorithm)\n16: - Public key loaded from environment variable (`PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`)\n17: - Bearer token format extraction and validation\n18: - Token expiration checking with 1-minute leeway\n19: - Protection of `/api/*` routes with authentication middleware\n20: - Public access to `/health` endpoint for Kubernetes probes\n21: - Structured error responses for all authentication failures\n22: - Request body size limiting (32MB) after authentication\n23: - Concurrent-safe public key access with read-write mutex\n24: - Comprehensive error handling and logging\n25: \n26: ## Architecture\n27: \n28: ### Package Structure\n29: \n30: ```\n31: pkg/picod/\n32: ├── auth.go                # AuthManager, AuthClaims, token validation\n33: ├── middleware.go          # AuthMiddleware, request interception\n34: ├── errors.go              # Error types, status code mapping (extended)\n35: ├── constants.go           # Environment variables, error messages (extended)\n36: ├── server.go              # Server integration, auth manager initialization (modified)\n37: ├── auth_test.go           # Unit tests for authentication\n38: └── server_test.go         # Integration tests (extended)\n39: \n40: changes/AR-017/\n41: ├── design.md              # This document\n42: ├── spec.md                # API specification\n43: ├── proposal.md            # Design proposal\n44: ├── delta-spec.md          # Detailed requirements\n45: ├── CHANGE.md              # Change log\n46: └── README.md              # Implementation notes\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Component Interactions\n50: \n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 1187. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n\n## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Implement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for PicoD, providing secure session authentication for the AgentCube platform by validating incoming request tokens and protecting sensitive API endpoints.\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD JWT middleware provides a comprehensive authentication layer that validates JWT tokens using RSA public key verification. The middleware intercepts all requests to protected API endpoints, extracts and validates Bearer tokens from the Authorization header, and ensures only properly authenticated requests can access file operations and code execution APIs. The implementation follows RFC 6750 Bearer Token usage standards and RS256 signature verification with clock skew tolerance.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- JWT token validation using RSA public key (RS256 algorithm)\n- Public key loaded from environment variable (`PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`)\n- Bearer token format extraction and validation\n- Token expiration checking with 1-minute leeway\n- Protection of `/api/*` routes with authentication middleware\n- Public access to `/health` endpoint for Kubernetes probes","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775860888122,"end":1775860888132}}}}
